WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:13.119 --> 00:00:14.800
[suspenseful music playing]

3
00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.200
[water bubbles]

4
00:01:14.079 --> 00:01:17.640
["Ayee" by Belvia playing]

5
00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:19.680
[seagulls squawking]

6
00:01:29.519 --> 00:01:31.680
["Ayee" by Belvia continues]

7
00:01:47.519 --> 00:01:48.840
[indistinct chatter]

8
00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:50.959
[in Kamtok] Please.

9
00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:53.719
There is enough fish for everyone.

10
00:01:53.799 --> 00:01:57.120
-You have to serve me first.
-No. I was here first.

11
00:01:57.599 --> 00:02:00.680
Ekah. you need to serve me.
I live far off.

12
00:02:00.760 --> 00:02:03.159
Yes. yes. I know who
came first and who was last.

13
00:02:03.959 --> 00:02:05.079
OK. let's do this--

14
00:02:05.159 --> 00:02:07.959
whoever stands in line.
will get extra fish.

15
00:02:08.039 --> 00:02:08.879
[woman] Yes.

16
00:02:14.919 --> 00:02:16.039
How much do you need?

17
00:02:18.039 --> 00:02:20.800
[music continues]

18
00:02:36.960 --> 00:02:37.840
[in English] Wow!

19
00:02:38.639 --> 00:02:39.759
Eighteen thousand?

20
00:02:41.599 --> 00:02:43.199
[in Kamtok] Business was good today.

21
00:02:49.159 --> 00:02:50.879
[in English] See. take this one.

22
00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:52.159
[in Kamtok] Buy something for yourself.

23
00:02:52.639 --> 00:02:53.919
-Papa!
-Take it!

24
00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:57.039
Keep it! You need it more than I do.

25
00:03:03.919 --> 00:03:05.240
Oh! My "little mother."

26
00:03:05.719 --> 00:03:07.840
This business would be nothing
without you.

27
00:03:08.879 --> 00:03:10.039
[in English] Thank you.
[in Kamtok] Thank you.

28
00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:12.840
[in English] We'll go house.

29
00:03:12.919 --> 00:03:13.840
We'll go house.

30
00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:15.360
Huh.

31
00:03:18.120 --> 00:03:21.719
[music continues]

32
00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:09.080
[groaning sound]

33
00:04:31.199 --> 00:04:32.040
Mommy.

34
00:04:32.519 --> 00:04:34.839
[breathes heavily]

35
00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:36.720
[groans]

36
00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:41.439
[in Kamtok] Sorry.

37
00:04:46.639 --> 00:04:47.639
[weakly. in English] Water.

38
00:04:50.959 --> 00:04:52.160
Water.

39
00:05:10.480 --> 00:05:11.800
["Free" by Belvia playing]

40
00:05:11.879 --> 00:05:15.519
♪ I am guilty of everything
that's happened around me ♪

41
00:05:16.040 --> 00:05:18.839
♪ And everything
I've been through lately ♪

42
00:05:19.360 --> 00:05:22.199
♪ His hands are dirty. sore ♪

43
00:05:24.120 --> 00:05:28.519
♪ Yet I am guilty for how I've gone ♪

44
00:05:29.160 --> 00:05:32.000
♪ And how much I've learned ♪

45
00:05:32.079 --> 00:05:34.879
♪ Not a wall would know me ♪

46
00:05:35.399 --> 00:05:37.920
♪ Oh. bye-bye ♪

47
00:05:38.639 --> 00:05:41.000
♪ Now you're givin' me power ♪

48
00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:43.839
♪ Now you're givin' me strength ♪

49
00:05:44.759 --> 00:05:47.160
♪ You said I am free ♪

50
00:05:48.519 --> 00:05:50.720
-♪ Oh. bye-bye... ♪
-[song fades]

51
00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:54.240
[in Kamtok] Why the stare. Papa?

52
00:05:54.800 --> 00:05:56.240
Because the fish is well roasted.

53
00:05:58.040 --> 00:05:59.199
The fish is very delicious.

54
00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:08.720
[fire crackling]

55
00:06:21.759 --> 00:06:23.519
[in English] You know why
we give you the name. Ekah?

56
00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:26.720
Yes. Papa.

57
00:06:27.279 --> 00:06:28.240
Why'd we give you that name?

58
00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:30.800
[in Kamtok]
Because it was your mother's name.

59
00:06:32.319 --> 00:06:33.160
Hmm.

60
00:06:40.519 --> 00:06:43.839
When I look at you.
all I see is my mother.

61
00:06:45.639 --> 00:06:46.879
You look just like her.

62
00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:52.160
[in English] Even the way you burn
this fish. you burn it like my mama.

63
00:06:53.360 --> 00:06:54.240
Papa!

64
00:06:59.399 --> 00:07:00.959
[in Kamtok] If I don't take care of you.

65
00:07:01.800 --> 00:07:02.680
who will?

66
00:07:05.399 --> 00:07:06.360
Hmm.

67
00:07:18.759 --> 00:07:20.959
I want you to know. our hard work.

68
00:07:22.199 --> 00:07:23.040
is not in vain.

69
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:25.279
[in English] People notice.

70
00:07:27.360 --> 00:07:28.560
Hmm.

71
00:07:28.639 --> 00:07:30.800
[in Kamtok] If you ask for the top
three fish people in this village...

72
00:07:30.879 --> 00:07:32.279
[in English] ...they will call my name.

73
00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:35.199
And when they call my name.
they will call your name. too.

74
00:07:37.240 --> 00:07:39.480
Eh? You do fine work.

75
00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:41.959
[in Kamtok] Keep up the good work.

76
00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:45.720
[Ekah. in English] Yes. Papa.

77
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:54.439
Papa. if I ask you something...

78
00:07:56.040 --> 00:07:56.879
Hmm.

79
00:07:57.959 --> 00:07:59.680
You be like your mommy plenty now?

80
00:08:01.160 --> 00:08:02.480
[in Kamtok] Most definitely.

81
00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:05.920
[in English] I be like my mama plenty.

82
00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:10.600
[in Kamtok] Do you love my mother?

83
00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:20.600
You are too young to understand.

84
00:08:22.040 --> 00:08:23.120
When you grow up.

85
00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:25.000
you will understand.

86
00:08:27.639 --> 00:08:29.480
[in English] When you grow. we will talk.

87
00:08:29.560 --> 00:08:30.639
[in Kamtok] Do you hear me?

88
00:08:31.439 --> 00:08:32.559
[in English] Don't worry.

89
00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:34.600
[in Kamtok] Eat!

90
00:08:51.039 --> 00:08:51.879
My "little mother."

91
00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:55.200
Papa.

92
00:08:55.279 --> 00:08:56.240
Welcome.

93
00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:57.639
[in English] Fine works. mama.

94
00:08:58.159 --> 00:08:59.000
Fine work.

95
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:04.039
[baby crying]

96
00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:05.000
Give me that bucket.

97
00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:07.159
Give me.

98
00:09:08.279 --> 00:09:09.120
Papa.

99
00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:11.279
-[crying continues]
-[man speaking indistinctly]

100
00:09:15.559 --> 00:09:17.360
[in Kamtok]
I don't want to ever leave you.

101
00:09:21.919 --> 00:09:23.919
This can never happen to you.

102
00:09:25.679 --> 00:09:27.320
You will not be a slave.
in any man's house.

103
00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:29.360
Huh!

104
00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:33.360
The teacher is waiting for her fish.
Rush there.

105
00:09:34.879 --> 00:09:35.720
Hmm.

106
00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:41.240
Quickly. don't be late.

107
00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:42.679
Huh.

108
00:09:53.639 --> 00:09:58.159
[school kids singing]

109
00:10:19.759 --> 00:10:20.759
[teacher] Ekah.

110
00:10:25.440 --> 00:10:26.279
Ekah.

111
00:10:29.360 --> 00:10:30.200
Ekah!

112
00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:32.559
Teacher.

113
00:10:33.159 --> 00:10:34.440
[in English] I have been calling.

114
00:10:34.519 --> 00:10:36.120
[in Kamtok] I brought your fish.

115
00:10:40.519 --> 00:10:42.320
[in English] This fish is too small.

116
00:10:42.799 --> 00:10:44.120
[in Kamtok] That's how you always buy it.

117
00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:46.279
[in English] Are you kidding me?
This fish is small.

118
00:10:46.360 --> 00:10:48.919
I've been buying from Solomon.
he should understand.

119
00:10:49.919 --> 00:10:52.000
It's too small. Look.

120
00:10:52.559 --> 00:10:53.480
[smacks lips]

121
00:10:58.080 --> 00:10:58.919
Here.

122
00:11:11.480 --> 00:11:12.679
Careful.

123
00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:23.919
[Solomon. in Kamtok]
The teacher wasn't in school?

124
00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:25.440
She was. Papa.

125
00:11:26.080 --> 00:11:27.480
[in English] Then why waste time so?

126
00:11:28.279 --> 00:11:32.000
[in Kamtok] Papa. I saw kids singing
school songs. I love it.

127
00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:37.720
How much Kiki's mother owe us?

128
00:11:41.080 --> 00:11:42.879
[in English]
Six thousand five hundred. Papa.

129
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:45.159
[in Kamtok]
Huh. go and call your Uncle Lucas.

130
00:11:45.240 --> 00:11:46.679
Tell him to come fast...

131
00:11:46.759 --> 00:11:48.039
Let's go and collect that debt.

132
00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:48.960
OK?

133
00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:50.799
Don't take too long.

134
00:11:50.879 --> 00:11:52.159
[in English] You hear me?

135
00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:58.120
["Yayayo" by Awu playing]

136
00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.080
[woman] I go see Barbara yesterday.

137
00:12:00.799 --> 00:12:03.960
[in Kamtok] She might die very soon.

138
00:12:04.399 --> 00:12:06.720
-Are you serious?
-I'm very serious.

139
00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:10.080
Death is calling her name.

140
00:12:11.399 --> 00:12:12.840
She will leave us soon.

141
00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:16.279
Die with all of that education?

142
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:18.759
You sound like education is important.

143
00:12:19.200 --> 00:12:20.720
Education is useless.

144
00:12:22.279 --> 00:12:24.120
It destroys families.

145
00:12:24.200 --> 00:12:29.519
Only lazy and stupid people go to school.

146
00:12:31.080 --> 00:12:35.200
Everyone I know in this village.
who dared to be educated is poor. ma.

147
00:12:37.159 --> 00:12:39.879
[in English] Lisa! You sure?

148
00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:40.919
I would lie you?

149
00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:43.080
OK.

150
00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:47.120
See. eh. that lazy boy. Peter.

151
00:12:47.720 --> 00:12:49.440
[in Kamtok]
He still lives with his parents.

152
00:12:50.399 --> 00:12:52.600
No pocket money.

153
00:12:52.679 --> 00:12:54.159
[in English] Joe too. the same thing.

154
00:12:54.639 --> 00:12:59.720
[in Kamtok]
Foolish Barbara decided to join them. too.

155
00:12:59.799 --> 00:13:03.480
Barbara's case is heart-breaking.
[in English] A long story.

156
00:13:04.399 --> 00:13:06.200
A long story for Barbara.

157
00:13:06.279 --> 00:13:08.000
[in Kamtok] Talk less of Rita...

158
00:13:08.399 --> 00:13:11.600
She went to school to study.
and instead got pregnant.

159
00:13:11.679 --> 00:13:14.000
[in English] Yes. yes. yes. Rita!

160
00:13:14.919 --> 00:13:15.759
[sighs]

161
00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:16.679
Rita!

162
00:13:16.759 --> 00:13:18.559
[girl. in Kamtok]
Mama. you know I hate school.

163
00:13:18.639 --> 00:13:22.720
I prefer to be a fish girl
rather than go to school.

164
00:13:22.799 --> 00:13:24.480
Or even get married like Aunty Rita.

165
00:13:24.559 --> 00:13:25.919
Smart thinking. Andong.

166
00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:27.840
You are a smart girl.

167
00:13:30.279 --> 00:13:34.759
I will buy you garri.
so you can eat it with fish.

168
00:13:35.600 --> 00:13:38.960
["Yayayo" by Awu continues]

169
00:13:42.639 --> 00:13:43.919
[groans]

170
00:13:50.159 --> 00:13:52.320
-Mommy?
-[groan]

171
00:13:52.919 --> 00:13:53.879
Mommy!

172
00:14:01.960 --> 00:14:04.120
Mommy. Mommy!

173
00:14:05.279 --> 00:14:06.279
Papa!

174
00:14:08.039 --> 00:14:09.039
Mommy.

175
00:14:09.919 --> 00:14:10.919
[groaning]

176
00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:12.759
Mommy! Papa!

177
00:14:17.679 --> 00:14:18.679
Mommy.

178
00:14:20.279 --> 00:14:21.559
[groans. wheezing]

179
00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:25.759
Papa! Mommy.

180
00:14:29.240 --> 00:14:31.480
Mommy. Pa--

181
00:14:37.600 --> 00:14:38.440
Pa--

182
00:14:44.039 --> 00:14:45.440
[crying]

183
00:14:47.559 --> 00:14:49.799
[sobbing]

184
00:14:53.240 --> 00:14:56.200
["Help Me" by Belvia playing]

185
00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:19.039
[sobbing continues]

186
00:15:23.120 --> 00:15:25.960
["Help Me" by Belvia continues]

187
00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:31.240
[rooster crows]

188
00:16:31.320 --> 00:16:33.799
[soft music playing]

189
00:16:51.039 --> 00:16:55.399
[in Kamtok] Solo.
how did you find this beautiful place?

190
00:16:56.799 --> 00:16:59.720
[in English]
I'm a fisherman! I'm a fisherman!

191
00:17:07.559 --> 00:17:08.720
[in Kamtok] It was here...

192
00:17:08.799 --> 00:17:11.319
[in English] ...when my papa ask
my mama. if they can marry.

193
00:17:12.240 --> 00:17:13.200
You like. huh?

194
00:17:13.279 --> 00:17:15.400
[in Kamtok] Yes. it is very beautiful.

195
00:17:17.599 --> 00:17:19.160
[in English] So...

196
00:17:20.480 --> 00:17:21.519
what will we do today?

197
00:17:24.279 --> 00:17:25.480
Barbara. I like you.

198
00:17:27.039 --> 00:17:28.680
And the way I like you.

199
00:17:29.599 --> 00:17:31.200
only in calculator it will show up.

200
00:17:31.279 --> 00:17:32.880
Aww. Solo.

201
00:17:35.079 --> 00:17:36.319
The way I like you...

202
00:17:37.519 --> 00:17:39.759
[in Kamtok]
...even a calculator cannot show it.

203
00:17:39.839 --> 00:17:41.039
[both laugh]

204
00:17:41.119 --> 00:17:44.519
["E Go Betta" by Mr. Leo playing]

205
00:17:47.519 --> 00:17:48.480
[in English] See...

206
00:17:49.119 --> 00:17:50.839
[in Kamtok] You know.
I cannot make a good family.

207
00:17:51.359 --> 00:17:52.759
if I don't have a good wife.

208
00:17:54.359 --> 00:17:56.640
[in English] You are the woman
who done touched my heart.

209
00:17:57.599 --> 00:17:58.640
[chuckles]

210
00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:02.119
Any time I look inside your eyes.

211
00:18:03.279 --> 00:18:05.359
my body just makes some kind...

212
00:18:07.200 --> 00:18:08.440
I like you. Barbara.

213
00:18:11.759 --> 00:18:13.240
I want you to be my woman.

214
00:18:14.599 --> 00:18:18.200
Be my woman. we could make
some fine family. me and you.

215
00:18:21.240 --> 00:18:23.240
That I dream about.
you know. ever since...

216
00:18:24.079 --> 00:18:25.960
Make me your woman. Solo.

217
00:18:27.359 --> 00:18:28.960
I will be your woman.

218
00:18:29.559 --> 00:18:31.400
-[in Kamtok] Is that a yes?
-[in English] Yes!

219
00:18:31.480 --> 00:18:32.480
[both laugh]

220
00:18:36.920 --> 00:18:39.960
[in Kamtok]
You see why I say you melt my heart?

221
00:18:40.480 --> 00:18:42.240
[both laugh]

222
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:47.440
Thank you for the beautiful shoes.
I like them a lot.

223
00:18:48.079 --> 00:18:50.720
[in English] Ah!
I could do everything for my Barbara.

224
00:18:58.440 --> 00:19:02.359
["Musica" by Vernyuy Tina playing]

225
00:22:35.279 --> 00:22:36.279
Teacher.

226
00:22:37.880 --> 00:22:39.079
What are you doing here?

227
00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:45.880
What's that?

228
00:22:46.799 --> 00:22:47.799
Let me see.

229
00:23:00.519 --> 00:23:02.240
[Ekah. in Kamtok] What is she saying?

230
00:23:06.880 --> 00:23:07.960
[in English] "One child.

231
00:23:08.880 --> 00:23:09.920
one teacher.

232
00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:11.880
one book.

233
00:23:12.680 --> 00:23:14.920
and one pen. can change the world."

234
00:23:18.559 --> 00:23:21.000
"If one man can destroy the world.

235
00:23:22.319 --> 00:23:24.119
why can't one girl...

236
00:23:26.119 --> 00:23:27.119
...change it?"

237
00:23:33.359 --> 00:23:35.559
[in Kamtok] Wh-- What is her name?

238
00:23:35.680 --> 00:23:37.400
[in English] She is called Malala.

239
00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:22.079
[Solomon] Ekah!

240
00:24:22.160 --> 00:24:23.160
Papa.

241
00:24:23.240 --> 00:24:24.519
[in Kamtok] What will you do?

242
00:24:50.240 --> 00:24:51.559
This is what killed your mother.

243
00:25:31.119 --> 00:25:31.960
Have you eaten?

244
00:25:33.519 --> 00:25:34.400
OK.

245
00:25:35.160 --> 00:25:36.079
Help take off my shoes.

246
00:25:47.559 --> 00:25:49.000
I have saved some money.

247
00:25:49.799 --> 00:25:52.039
I will buy you a new fish band next month.
OK?

248
00:25:53.480 --> 00:25:55.079
So you can roast fish very well.

249
00:26:22.920 --> 00:26:25.079
Your father go. see a friend.

250
00:26:27.119 --> 00:26:28.079
Ekah.

251
00:26:28.160 --> 00:26:30.039
-[in Kamtok] Yes. uncle.
-You are a very good child.

252
00:26:31.960 --> 00:26:34.119
Everyone is proud of you.

253
00:26:36.799 --> 00:26:38.319
[in English] Thank-- Thank you. uncle.

254
00:26:39.119 --> 00:26:40.920
If one of my three boy. them.

255
00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:42.480
they cook like you so.

256
00:26:42.559 --> 00:26:44.119
I would have been a happy man.

257
00:26:45.920 --> 00:26:48.240
[in Kamtok]
Your father is very respected here.

258
00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:49.920
because of you.

259
00:26:53.440 --> 00:26:55.319
[in English] No change. eh.
[in Kamtok] You should never change.

260
00:26:57.279 --> 00:26:58.640
Let me rush to work.

261
00:26:58.720 --> 00:26:59.559
Uh...

262
00:26:59.640 --> 00:27:00.480
Ekah!

263
00:27:01.079 --> 00:27:07.079
Have you ever asked yourself
why all these educated kids are poor?

264
00:27:08.119 --> 00:27:09.440
They are lazy kids.

265
00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:13.599
You understand? They are very lazy kids.

266
00:27:13.680 --> 00:27:16.480
Education is not for women.

267
00:27:18.920 --> 00:27:20.880
All right. Think about this.

268
00:27:23.200 --> 00:27:25.920
Has an educated person
ever bought fish from you.

269
00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:31.279
without arguing the price?

270
00:27:33.720 --> 00:27:34.720
Huh?

271
00:27:37.559 --> 00:27:39.480
They are poor. We even feed them.

272
00:27:42.119 --> 00:27:42.960
Yes. we do.

273
00:27:44.599 --> 00:27:48.359
Stay just the way you are.
We like you as you are.

274
00:27:48.440 --> 00:27:49.279
[in English] Not change.

275
00:27:50.079 --> 00:27:52.400
[in Kamtok]
Let nobody deceive you with education.

276
00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:53.960
Education is bad for women.

277
00:27:55.559 --> 00:27:56.559
You understand?

278
00:28:02.559 --> 00:28:03.519
Let me rush to work.

279
00:28:13.119 --> 00:28:14.119
[Andong] Ekah.

280
00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:18.720
[Ekah] Andong.

281
00:28:19.359 --> 00:28:21.759
-[both in Kamtok] How are you?
-I'm all right.

282
00:28:22.519 --> 00:28:23.680
Ekah.

283
00:28:23.759 --> 00:28:26.039
My uncle came back yesterday.

284
00:28:26.960 --> 00:28:30.640
He says I will start school on Monday.

285
00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:34.759
I don't want to go to school.
Please. give me an excuse to tell him.

286
00:28:35.799 --> 00:28:37.200
I hate school.

287
00:28:47.480 --> 00:28:48.400
Andong.

288
00:28:48.480 --> 00:28:51.599
Sorry. I have to go.
We'll talk some other time.

289
00:28:52.920 --> 00:28:57.000
["Ayagayo" by Salatiel playing]

290
00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:12.200
♪ I woke up with a good vibe ♪

291
00:29:13.759 --> 00:29:16.440
♪ Closed my eyes and saw a good sign ♪

292
00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:20.480
♪ Something different
Something too nice ♪

293
00:29:21.640 --> 00:29:24.599
♪ This life we living no be two times ♪

294
00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:30.039
♪ If you know then you know
If you no know then you no know ♪

295
00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:33.599
♪ Don't worry about it ♪

296
00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:35.480
♪ If i' show then i' show... ♪

297
00:29:35.559 --> 00:29:37.039
[in English] Why you wake up late. so?

298
00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:39.839
[in Kamtok]
You had too much work yesterday?

299
00:29:41.119 --> 00:29:42.680
I slept late.

300
00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:45.240
I have repaired the engine.

301
00:29:45.720 --> 00:29:47.599
The new kick-starter is working fine.

302
00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:53.160
♪ Good times don't come easy ♪

303
00:29:53.240 --> 00:29:55.160
♪ But they do ♪

304
00:29:55.240 --> 00:30:00.720
-♪ Just remember. please to sing ♪
-♪ Ayo. Ayo. Ayo ♪

305
00:30:00.799 --> 00:30:02.720
♪ Ayaga yagayo ♪

306
00:30:02.799 --> 00:30:04.720
♪ Ayo Ayo ♪

307
00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:10.880
♪ Ayo. Ayo. Ayo. Ayaga yagayo ♪

308
00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:12.799
♪ Ayo Ayo ♪

309
00:30:13.559 --> 00:30:16.839
♪ I can see people smiling ♪

310
00:30:16.920 --> 00:30:18.920
♪ Aya Gaya Gayo ♪

311
00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:21.000
♪ Music playing ♪

312
00:30:21.079 --> 00:30:22.799
♪ Aya Gaya Gayo ♪

313
00:30:22.880 --> 00:30:25.119
♪ Children dancing ♪

314
00:30:25.200 --> 00:30:26.640
♪ Aya Gaya Gayo ♪

315
00:30:26.720 --> 00:30:29.160
♪ My people happy ♪

316
00:30:29.240 --> 00:30:31.440
♪ Aya Gaya Gayo... ♪

317
00:30:31.519 --> 00:30:32.359
[woman] Ekah.

318
00:30:33.960 --> 00:30:34.880
Ekah!

319
00:30:35.759 --> 00:30:36.920
Ekah! [clapping hands]

320
00:30:37.559 --> 00:30:39.319
[in Kamtok]
Hah. are you OK?

321
00:30:40.039 --> 00:30:41.559
-What did you say?
-Where is your father?

322
00:30:47.359 --> 00:30:48.200
Ekah!

323
00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:50.240
Where is your father?

324
00:30:51.839 --> 00:30:53.400
♪ Oh yes indeed. yes indeed ♪

325
00:30:53.480 --> 00:30:55.200
♪ You know that I got a vibe ♪

326
00:30:55.279 --> 00:30:59.599
♪ But if you know then you know
If you no know then you no know ♪

327
00:31:00.640 --> 00:31:03.400
♪ Don't worry about it ♪

328
00:31:03.480 --> 00:31:05.480
♪ And if i' go then i' go... ♪

329
00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:07.839
[woman in Kamtok]
Please serve my fish. I have to go.

330
00:31:08.920 --> 00:31:10.279
Madam. I beg you.

331
00:31:10.359 --> 00:31:11.960
If you can't wait.
then you go to a different place.

332
00:31:13.039 --> 00:31:14.200
What did you say?

333
00:31:14.680 --> 00:31:17.680
[in English] I said. if you no feel wait.
then you go different place.

334
00:31:20.599 --> 00:31:22.559
[in Kamtok] I'm leaving.
[in English] Give my money.

335
00:31:23.559 --> 00:31:24.720
[Ekah] Which money?

336
00:31:24.799 --> 00:31:26.799
[in Kamtok] Didn't I pay you?
[in English] Give my balance.

337
00:31:27.799 --> 00:31:29.680
Madam. I beg no just start.

338
00:31:29.759 --> 00:31:32.319
[in Kamtok] You never give me nothing.
and you can't trick me. Never!

339
00:31:32.400 --> 00:31:33.440
-Eh?
-[Solomon] Ekah!

340
00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:45.519
-Madam. please don't be mad.
-If not for you. I would have left.

341
00:31:45.599 --> 00:31:48.359
-I'll serve you-- she forgot.
-It is only because of you.

342
00:31:48.839 --> 00:31:49.680
Don't be angry. please understand.

343
00:31:49.759 --> 00:31:50.880
I have heard you.

344
00:31:50.960 --> 00:31:52.880
[in English] She buy fish for 3.000.

345
00:31:52.960 --> 00:31:54.839
She give 5.000. Give balance.

346
00:31:58.480 --> 00:31:59.960
[in Kamtok] So. she even has the change.

347
00:32:05.759 --> 00:32:07.720
Please don't be angry. Please understand.

348
00:32:11.160 --> 00:32:12.400
Have you been served?

349
00:32:12.480 --> 00:32:13.480
Serve me!

350
00:32:26.960 --> 00:32:27.799
Lucas.

351
00:32:27.880 --> 00:32:28.759
Huh.

352
00:32:29.599 --> 00:32:30.440
Sule.

353
00:32:33.400 --> 00:32:34.400
[in Kamtok] Welcome.

354
00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:37.039
Mustapha. How are you?

355
00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:40.839
Huh?

356
00:32:41.480 --> 00:32:42.319
What is it?

357
00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:43.880
[in English] Give me my money.

358
00:32:46.039 --> 00:32:46.960
Hah.

359
00:32:47.039 --> 00:32:48.200
[in Kamtok] This is a joke. right?

360
00:32:48.720 --> 00:32:49.759
[in English] You know time?

361
00:32:51.839 --> 00:32:54.599
[in Kamtok] Lucas. I didn't come here
to joke with you.

362
00:32:56.279 --> 00:32:57.119
[smacks lips]

363
00:32:57.640 --> 00:32:59.400
You can't ask for a debt. at this time.

364
00:32:59.480 --> 00:33:00.559
Ah-ah.

365
00:33:00.640 --> 00:33:03.000
I gave you the money in these times.

366
00:33:05.160 --> 00:33:06.160
[in English] Anyway...

367
00:33:08.640 --> 00:33:10.880
[in Kamtok] Based on calculations.
I can only pay you next month.

368
00:33:11.359 --> 00:33:12.680
I don't have the money now.

369
00:33:13.160 --> 00:33:15.519
[in Kamtok]
Lucas. enough of your stupid jokes.

370
00:33:16.799 --> 00:33:17.839
Do you see me laughing?

371
00:33:18.440 --> 00:33:20.799
I am not joking. I don't have money.
Next month.

372
00:33:21.720 --> 00:33:23.079
Lucas. you are a liar.

373
00:33:23.720 --> 00:33:24.759
[in English] Lucas. you lie.

374
00:33:25.319 --> 00:33:28.400
[in Kamtok] Don't we see you selling
coconut water by the sea every day?

375
00:33:29.200 --> 00:33:30.279
How can he talk this?

376
00:33:31.119 --> 00:33:32.960
[in English] Who give you the power
to come to my compound.

377
00:33:33.039 --> 00:33:33.920
and curse me?

378
00:33:34.359 --> 00:33:35.200
I do owe you?

379
00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:37.279
I do owe you?

380
00:33:37.359 --> 00:33:40.720
[in Kamtok]
Lucas. Mustapha is telling the truth.

381
00:33:41.319 --> 00:33:44.160
You cannot dribble me
like Samuel Eto'o. on a football pitch.

382
00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:47.799
Lucas. if you don't pay my money...

383
00:33:49.119 --> 00:33:50.720
you will be dead.

384
00:33:52.680 --> 00:33:53.680
Hmm...

385
00:33:54.759 --> 00:33:56.640
[in English] You come my house.
you can't threaten me.

386
00:33:59.440 --> 00:34:01.160
[in Kamtok] Sule. Look...

387
00:34:02.160 --> 00:34:03.359
[in English] I go cover my eye...

388
00:34:03.960 --> 00:34:05.519
I'll count from one to five.

389
00:34:05.599 --> 00:34:07.640
[in Kamtok] When I open my eyes.
and you're still here.

390
00:34:07.720 --> 00:34:08.599
I promise you...

391
00:34:10.480 --> 00:34:11.719
one of you will be dead.

392
00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:15.360
[in English] One.

393
00:34:17.079 --> 00:34:17.920
Two.

394
00:34:20.480 --> 00:34:21.320
Three.

395
00:34:22.880 --> 00:34:23.719
Four.

396
00:34:25.360 --> 00:34:26.199
Five.

397
00:34:29.119 --> 00:34:30.840
No. Sule?

398
00:34:31.559 --> 00:34:32.800
Eh. what is this?

399
00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:34.239
[in Kamtok] You don't know how to joke?

400
00:34:34.960 --> 00:34:35.840
[in English] Eh. my brother.

401
00:34:35.920 --> 00:34:38.679
[in Kamtok] Let's fix this like men...

402
00:34:38.760 --> 00:34:40.360
Let's fix it like brothers.

403
00:34:41.639 --> 00:34:42.960
[in English] W-Why?

404
00:34:43.039 --> 00:34:46.800
[in Kamtok] My brother. you will be dead
if you don't pay my money.

405
00:34:48.360 --> 00:34:49.239
[in English] OK. OK.

406
00:34:49.920 --> 00:34:50.960
[in Kamtok] The money is in my pocket.

407
00:34:51.760 --> 00:34:52.679
[in English] My pocket.

408
00:35:00.400 --> 00:35:02.639
[in Kamtok] Let's fix this like brothers.

409
00:35:02.719 --> 00:35:03.559
Please.

410
00:35:07.360 --> 00:35:08.199
[in English] How much?

411
00:35:13.320 --> 00:35:14.239
It's 4.000.

412
00:35:15.079 --> 00:35:16.320
Four thousand?

413
00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:18.199
[in Kamtok] You owe me 70.000.

414
00:35:18.280 --> 00:35:19.400
[in English] Sule. that's all I have.

415
00:35:19.480 --> 00:35:22.000
I tell you...
you give me some time. no?

416
00:35:22.079 --> 00:35:23.239
[in Kamtok] That's all I have right now.

417
00:35:23.719 --> 00:35:25.880
Lucas. you must finish paying me my money.

418
00:35:27.239 --> 00:35:28.800
[in English] OK. You go take firewood?

419
00:35:28.880 --> 00:35:29.880
[scoffs]

420
00:35:31.519 --> 00:35:32.480
[in English] What?

421
00:35:32.559 --> 00:35:35.000
You're not gonna need to buy
firewood again for two year.

422
00:35:36.440 --> 00:35:37.320
I swear.

423
00:35:38.400 --> 00:35:39.239
[in Kamtok] Here is the wood.

424
00:35:42.360 --> 00:35:44.639
["Kuweh" by Achuo playing]

425
00:36:18.760 --> 00:36:20.800
[in Kamtok] Drink it while it's still hot.

426
00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:25.599
It will cure your cough. Drink it.

427
00:36:27.239 --> 00:36:28.239
[in English] Drink.

428
00:36:38.679 --> 00:36:40.039
Something that worry you?

429
00:36:44.840 --> 00:36:46.239
[in Kamtok] Is something disturbing you?

430
00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:48.280
You look worried.

431
00:36:51.719 --> 00:36:55.159
The misunderstanding with that
woman should not disturb you.

432
00:36:58.400 --> 00:36:59.239
OK?

433
00:36:59.960 --> 00:37:01.480
You were too busy.

434
00:37:02.079 --> 00:37:03.719
So you got confused.

435
00:37:04.280 --> 00:37:05.719
It can happen to anyone.

436
00:37:06.360 --> 00:37:08.840
Do you understand? Don't worry. drink up.

437
00:37:09.559 --> 00:37:12.400
Drink it before it gets cold
[in English] Drink.

438
00:37:16.519 --> 00:37:17.760
I want to go to school.

439
00:37:27.079 --> 00:37:29.000
School is not for fish people like we.

440
00:37:30.280 --> 00:37:31.400
And you being a woman.

441
00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:35.519
[in Kamtok] That is a bad idea.

442
00:37:38.639 --> 00:37:40.199
What will the villagers say?

443
00:37:44.559 --> 00:37:46.119
What will those same people say...

444
00:37:47.119 --> 00:37:50.159
when I go to school
and start making money?

445
00:37:51.599 --> 00:37:52.480
I mean. a lot of money.

446
00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:55.519
Nobody in this house
would need to go fishing.

447
00:37:55.599 --> 00:37:57.199
every day. 24/7.

448
00:37:57.719 --> 00:38:00.039
Our lives would be changed forever.

449
00:38:01.159 --> 00:38:02.119
Solo.

450
00:38:03.239 --> 00:38:05.039
They say.
a blind person cannot lead another.

451
00:38:07.000 --> 00:38:08.840
Fishing is for young people.

452
00:38:10.199 --> 00:38:11.199
[in English] OK.

453
00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:16.800
[in Kamtok] What would happen
when we got old and couldn't go fishing?

454
00:38:17.880 --> 00:38:20.039
God has blessed us with just one kid.

455
00:38:21.159 --> 00:38:22.480
And it's a girl.

456
00:38:28.719 --> 00:38:32.719
What God has blessed us with. is fishing.

457
00:38:34.199 --> 00:38:35.400
And we can't change it.

458
00:38:36.480 --> 00:38:37.599
I disagree with you.

459
00:38:42.400 --> 00:38:45.280
["Day &amp; Night" by Ewube playing]

460
00:38:58.880 --> 00:38:59.880
[slams door]

461
00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.400
[footsteps]

462
00:39:36.719 --> 00:39:37.639
[Solomon] My "little mother."

463
00:39:58.079 --> 00:39:59.760
[in English] You say you want
to go to school...

464
00:40:06.199 --> 00:40:10.039
You asked me the other time.
if I like your mama.

465
00:40:14.440 --> 00:40:16.039
[in Kamtok] Do you want
to know the answer now?

466
00:40:17.880 --> 00:40:18.840
Do you?

467
00:40:29.639 --> 00:40:31.559
[in English] I never ever liked my skin.

468
00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:37.599
[in Kamtok] Every love and care I had...

469
00:40:40.119 --> 00:40:41.400
I gave it to your mother.

470
00:40:43.239 --> 00:40:45.280
When my mother and brother Lucas

471
00:40:45.920 --> 00:40:47.679
tried to say anything bad about her.

472
00:40:48.440 --> 00:40:49.960
I kicked my mother out of the house.

473
00:40:53.440 --> 00:40:55.440
Nobody loves your mother more than me.

474
00:40:56.920 --> 00:40:57.760
I mean. nobody.

475
00:40:58.559 --> 00:40:59.400
Not even God.

476
00:41:02.519 --> 00:41:03.800
And not even you.

477
00:41:04.599 --> 00:41:05.639
You don't love her more than I do.

478
00:41:16.800 --> 00:41:19.360
It seems the devil took over her.

479
00:41:23.039 --> 00:41:25.119
She started talking to me
like a mad woman.

480
00:41:27.079 --> 00:41:28.320
[in English] My fiancé...

481
00:41:29.440 --> 00:41:33.400
has accepted to pay
every dime you spent on me.

482
00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:34.480
including interest.

483
00:41:34.559 --> 00:41:35.480
-I will pay you back.
-No. no. no.

484
00:41:35.559 --> 00:41:37.320
[in Kamtok]
No. you can't utter such words.

485
00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:39.199
I refuse to accept this.

486
00:41:40.199 --> 00:41:41.159
[in English] You are my woman!

487
00:41:42.639 --> 00:41:44.079
Try to understand. papa.

488
00:41:44.159 --> 00:41:45.039
I beg.

489
00:41:45.119 --> 00:41:46.039
[in Kamtok] Let me go.

490
00:41:48.000 --> 00:41:51.239
Is this what education does?

491
00:41:52.159 --> 00:41:55.440
-That man doesn't love you...
-Please. hold it!

492
00:41:56.159 --> 00:41:57.360
[in English] Do I look like a kid?

493
00:41:57.440 --> 00:41:58.960
Oh. you want to teach me about love?

494
00:41:59.440 --> 00:42:01.679
This whole place is a mental prison.

495
00:42:02.960 --> 00:42:05.320
I wouldn't want her to suffocate
in this madness.

496
00:42:16.840 --> 00:42:18.000
I will die first...

497
00:42:18.760 --> 00:42:20.360
[in Kamtok] ...than let you make
the same mistakes as your mother.

498
00:42:22.480 --> 00:42:23.679
[in English] No happen.

499
00:42:23.760 --> 00:42:26.559
[in Kamtok]
You hear me? You hear me?!

500
00:42:27.440 --> 00:42:28.760
[in English]
No happen again.

501
00:42:30.880 --> 00:42:31.840
Not going to happen.

502
00:42:32.960 --> 00:42:36.679
["Day &amp; Night" by Ewube continues]

503
00:43:20.920 --> 00:43:21.760
Ekah.

504
00:43:23.280 --> 00:43:24.119
Andong.

505
00:43:26.199 --> 00:43:27.039
[in Kamtok] I'm sorry.

506
00:43:27.719 --> 00:43:29.519
-[in English] Thank you.
-[in Kamtok] I'm sorry. too.

507
00:43:32.119 --> 00:43:32.960
Where is your mother?

508
00:43:33.719 --> 00:43:34.679
She went out.

509
00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:41.119
Didn't you say
you do not want to go to school?

510
00:43:41.760 --> 00:43:44.440
My uncle came yesterday.

511
00:43:45.039 --> 00:43:47.360
and made a big deal out of it.

512
00:43:50.039 --> 00:43:50.920
About what?

513
00:43:52.400 --> 00:43:55.360
When my father died in the fishing waters.

514
00:43:55.440 --> 00:43:58.079
my uncle promised to send me to school.

515
00:43:59.159 --> 00:44:01.440
He has been sending money for school fees.

516
00:44:01.519 --> 00:44:02.840
but my mom has been spending it.

517
00:44:03.679 --> 00:44:06.400
Yesterday. after the fight.

518
00:44:06.480 --> 00:44:09.159
he bought me two uniforms.

519
00:44:09.239 --> 00:44:12.920
then this morning he went
and paid my school fees.

520
00:44:18.199 --> 00:44:19.119
How was it?

521
00:44:20.199 --> 00:44:21.039
What?

522
00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:22.599
[in English] School.

523
00:44:25.239 --> 00:44:26.320
[in Kamtok] It was boring.

524
00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:29.280
I had no idea what the teacher was saying.

525
00:44:29.360 --> 00:44:32.000
[in English] One divided by two.

526
00:44:32.079 --> 00:44:34.559
[in Kamtok] I was in class
but thinking about us.

527
00:44:35.039 --> 00:44:37.440
How we were free
and enjoying being by the seaside.

528
00:44:42.719 --> 00:44:44.159
[teacher. in English]
What are the factors of six?

529
00:44:52.079 --> 00:44:54.119
What are the factors of six?

530
00:44:56.800 --> 00:44:58.119
Who knows the answer?

531
00:45:01.719 --> 00:45:02.719
Anybody?

532
00:45:04.800 --> 00:45:06.800
-Say One.
-[pupils] One.

533
00:45:07.679 --> 00:45:10.000
[teacher]
Factors of six. I started with one.

534
00:45:11.159 --> 00:45:12.400
What would be the next?

535
00:45:13.119 --> 00:45:15.639
-Two.
-[pupils] Two.

536
00:45:15.719 --> 00:45:17.480
-Three.
-[pupils] Three.

537
00:45:17.559 --> 00:45:19.360
-Six...
-[pupils] Six.

538
00:45:19.880 --> 00:45:21.440
[teacher] So the factors of six will be...

539
00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:27.519
[pupils] One. two. three. six.

540
00:45:27.599 --> 00:45:29.760
So. we have learned the factors of six.

541
00:45:30.320 --> 00:45:31.159
Now...

542
00:45:36.280 --> 00:45:39.400
["Musica" by Vernyuy Tina playing]

543
00:46:50.440 --> 00:46:54.039
[in Kamtok] Take this 300 francs
and buy something for yourself.

544
00:46:54.119 --> 00:46:55.559
-[in English] Papa. thank you.
-Huh.

545
00:46:57.239 --> 00:47:01.039
-[in Kamtok] Go home and cook. I'm hungry.
-[in English] Papa. I already cooked.

546
00:47:02.440 --> 00:47:04.480
-How about dirty clothes then?
-Alreadty washed them.

547
00:47:05.519 --> 00:47:06.400
Hmm.

548
00:47:10.480 --> 00:47:13.400
[in Kamtok]
OK. Go home and have some deserved rest.

549
00:47:13.480 --> 00:47:14.719
Go rest.

550
00:47:19.079 --> 00:47:21.480
["Musica" by Vernyuy Tina continues]

551
00:48:55.320 --> 00:48:57.960
["Di Feng" by Lesline playing]

552
00:49:52.119 --> 00:49:56.079
[teacher. in English] If a boy takes
two hours to clear a hectare of land.

553
00:49:56.719 --> 00:50:01.440
how many minutes will four boys take
to clear that same portion of land?

554
00:50:03.239 --> 00:50:07.400
If a boy takes two hours
to clear a hectare of land.

555
00:50:08.079 --> 00:50:14.039
how many minutes will four boys take
to clear this same portion of land?

556
00:50:16.280 --> 00:50:19.760
-Two hours to clear a hectare of land...
-[Ekah] Thirty minutes!

557
00:50:21.360 --> 00:50:22.320
Who said that?

558
00:50:26.000 --> 00:50:26.840
Ekah?

559
00:50:28.039 --> 00:50:29.239
Wait! Ekah?

560
00:50:30.159 --> 00:50:32.280
Come. Come to class.

561
00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:15.280
I was thinking you'd forgotten about me.

562
00:51:17.960 --> 00:51:19.559
This fish keeps reducing every day.

563
00:51:19.639 --> 00:51:21.599
Are you sure this is fish
for 2.000 francs?

564
00:51:21.679 --> 00:51:22.639
Yes.

565
00:51:32.920 --> 00:51:33.920
Come this way.

566
00:51:38.199 --> 00:51:39.039
Careful.

567
00:51:47.519 --> 00:51:48.440
OK.

568
00:51:50.840 --> 00:51:51.679
It's OK.

569
00:51:52.679 --> 00:51:54.320
Oh. Your money. Sorry.

570
00:52:01.199 --> 00:52:02.199
Ekah.

571
00:52:05.000 --> 00:52:06.480
Who taught you arithmetic?

572
00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:11.320
-No man.
-Ekah. don't lie to me.

573
00:52:12.320 --> 00:52:16.000
You can't tell me you learnt arithmetic
by giving change to your customers.

574
00:52:16.719 --> 00:52:17.599
Tell me the truth.

575
00:52:20.559 --> 00:52:21.639
[in Kamtok] It's you.

576
00:52:22.760 --> 00:52:24.880
[in English] Me? How?

577
00:52:26.559 --> 00:52:28.880
[in Kamtok] I peep through
the window every day to learn.

578
00:52:32.920 --> 00:52:35.039
[in English]
Is that how you learned arithmetic?

579
00:52:41.760 --> 00:52:42.599
OK.

580
00:52:44.239 --> 00:52:49.519
If one girl takes one hour
to wash 50 plates...

581
00:52:50.639 --> 00:52:54.639
how long will three girls take to wash
those similar number of plates?

582
00:53:00.679 --> 00:53:01.679
Twenty minutes.

583
00:53:08.639 --> 00:53:10.199
Four people are standing in line.

584
00:53:11.800 --> 00:53:14.559
John is three meters behind Laura

585
00:53:15.280 --> 00:53:17.280
and two meters in front of Peter.

586
00:53:18.760 --> 00:53:21.800
Paul is four meters in front of Laura.

587
00:53:22.400 --> 00:53:24.880
What is the distance
between Peter and Paul?

588
00:53:32.119 --> 00:53:33.199
[stutters]

589
00:53:34.719 --> 00:53:35.679
Nine meters.

590
00:53:44.639 --> 00:53:46.679
Does your father know about this?

591
00:53:50.960 --> 00:53:52.559
OK. Bye.

592
00:53:53.880 --> 00:53:56.880
["Dege Dege" by Awu playing]

593
00:54:25.639 --> 00:54:27.639
-[in Kamtok] Brother.
-Hmm.

594
00:54:28.800 --> 00:54:30.119
I need your help.

595
00:54:31.360 --> 00:54:34.119
I need that money before the deadline.

596
00:54:35.400 --> 00:54:37.599
Lucas! 66.000.

597
00:54:38.480 --> 00:54:41.159
If I had that kind of money.
Ekah would get a new fish barn.

598
00:54:42.039 --> 00:54:44.519
I don't have it.

599
00:54:45.000 --> 00:54:45.920
Ekah's father.

600
00:54:48.079 --> 00:54:50.159
-Teacher Bihbih.
-[in English] Yes.

601
00:54:50.239 --> 00:54:51.679
-[in Kamtok] What are you doing here?
-[in English] Good afternoon.

602
00:54:55.400 --> 00:54:58.440
-Do I need permission?
-[in Kamtok] Not at all.

603
00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:04.920
Just that people like you
only come out on special occasions.

604
00:55:07.840 --> 00:55:10.119
[in English]
I came so that you and I could talk.

605
00:55:10.199 --> 00:55:11.760
Just the both of us.

606
00:55:14.360 --> 00:55:16.880
[in Kamtok] If you have anything to say.
tell him here.

607
00:55:17.480 --> 00:55:19.280
[in English]
I am not talking to you. please.

608
00:55:19.840 --> 00:55:24.360
[in Kamtok] Teacher Bihbih.
if there is something. just say it here.

609
00:55:25.119 --> 00:55:28.039
Have a seat.
so you can be offered a drink.

610
00:55:28.880 --> 00:55:30.800
-Have a seat.
-[in English] No. I'm fine. Thank you.

611
00:55:32.119 --> 00:55:33.039
Um...

612
00:55:33.599 --> 00:55:36.239
Actually. I came so that
you and I could talk something

613
00:55:36.320 --> 00:55:38.079
very important about your daughter.

614
00:55:39.400 --> 00:55:40.840
-My Ekah?
-Yes.

615
00:55:42.239 --> 00:55:44.079
[in Kamtok] In my family. we do not cheat.

616
00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:50.239
The fish we give you is the right size.

617
00:55:50.320 --> 00:55:51.639
[in English] Everything is fine.

618
00:55:51.719 --> 00:55:54.000
In fact. even better. Yes.

619
00:55:54.079 --> 00:55:55.159
[Solomon] Ah-hah.

620
00:55:55.239 --> 00:55:58.760
We thank God.
[in Kamtok] Have a glass of palm wine.

621
00:55:58.840 --> 00:55:59.920
I'm fine. Thank you.

622
00:56:06.719 --> 00:56:08.360
[in English] Ekah. Mr. Solomon.

623
00:56:09.079 --> 00:56:12.440
that child. she could be the next
big thing in this village.

624
00:56:18.000 --> 00:56:19.000
[clears throat]

625
00:56:21.480 --> 00:56:23.119
[in Kamtok] All this time that I taught.

626
00:56:24.000 --> 00:56:26.360
I had no idea Ekah
watched through a hole to learn.

627
00:56:29.639 --> 00:56:31.000
[in English]
My Ekah come to your school?

628
00:56:31.079 --> 00:56:32.159
Yes.

629
00:56:32.239 --> 00:56:33.320
-My Ekah?
-Yes.

630
00:56:34.320 --> 00:56:38.159
And the good thing about it is.
I asked some very hard question today...

631
00:56:38.239 --> 00:56:39.599
[in Kamtok] ...and she answered.

632
00:56:41.000 --> 00:56:42.119
[in English] Mr. Solomon.

633
00:56:43.480 --> 00:56:46.480
And to even be more sure.
I asked more question...

634
00:56:46.559 --> 00:56:47.800
[in Kamtok]
...and she answered all of them.

635
00:56:49.159 --> 00:56:50.159
Your daughter...

636
00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:52.960
was God-sent for your family.

637
00:56:54.880 --> 00:56:58.440
Are you out of your mind?

638
00:56:58.519 --> 00:57:01.159
[in English] I'm not joking.
I'm very serious.

639
00:57:02.480 --> 00:57:04.559
In fact.
you should get her enrolled in school.

640
00:57:05.559 --> 00:57:07.800
She could benefit from the opportunities.

641
00:57:07.880 --> 00:57:09.440
other people. in school.

642
00:57:10.559 --> 00:57:11.840
Mr. Solomon.

643
00:57:14.400 --> 00:57:15.400
Brother.

644
00:57:16.559 --> 00:57:19.519
[in Kamtok] Why do bad luck
always choose your house?

645
00:57:20.679 --> 00:57:22.840
[in English] Again and again.
[in Kamtok] Before it was Barbara.

646
00:57:23.960 --> 00:57:25.039
now. it's Ekah.

647
00:57:26.360 --> 00:57:27.360
[in English] Why?

648
00:57:29.639 --> 00:57:31.400
[in English] My Ekah go to school?

649
00:57:32.360 --> 00:57:33.199
My Ekah?

650
00:57:37.360 --> 00:57:38.480
-Mr. Solomon?
-Hey. hey. hey!

651
00:57:39.559 --> 00:57:40.400
[in Kamtok] What is it?

652
00:57:42.000 --> 00:57:44.000
Everywhere. school. school. school.

653
00:57:44.480 --> 00:57:46.960
If school was that good.
you will not be dressed like this.

654
00:57:48.119 --> 00:57:51.719
You look like a replica of Pinocchio!
Nonsense. sit down!

655
00:57:55.000 --> 00:57:55.840
[in English] Brother!

656
00:57:58.320 --> 00:58:00.280
[dramatic music playing]

657
00:58:09.920 --> 00:58:10.760
[screams]

658
00:58:10.840 --> 00:58:13.519
Papa. Papa. Papa. Papa...

659
00:58:13.599 --> 00:58:15.079
[screaming continues]

660
00:58:17.840 --> 00:58:19.360
[in Kamtok]
You want to become like your mother?

661
00:58:19.440 --> 00:58:20.840
-[in English] No. Papa. No.
-[in Kamtok] You want to be stubborn?

662
00:58:20.920 --> 00:58:22.119
Lay down there!

663
00:58:22.199 --> 00:58:23.239
I said. lay down!

664
00:58:23.320 --> 00:58:24.159
Lay down!

665
00:58:28.519 --> 00:58:29.599
[in English] No. Papa. please.

666
00:58:31.599 --> 00:58:32.480
[in Kamtok] Will you set your foot
in that school again?

667
00:58:32.559 --> 00:58:33.400
[in English] No. Papa.

668
00:58:33.480 --> 00:58:34.320
[in Kamtok]
Will you go to that class again?

669
00:58:34.400 --> 00:58:35.400
No. Papa! Never! [screams]

670
00:58:35.480 --> 00:58:37.199
-I can't hear you!
-I will never go there again. Papa!

671
00:58:37.280 --> 00:58:38.800
Will I see you in that school again?

672
00:58:38.880 --> 00:58:41.199
I will never go there again. Papa!
I promise!

673
00:58:41.280 --> 00:58:43.760
-I can't hear you.
-I promise. Papa!

674
00:58:43.840 --> 00:58:45.079
[crying]

675
00:58:45.159 --> 00:58:46.679
-You hear me?
-Yes. Papa.

676
00:58:52.840 --> 00:58:54.480
[crying continues]

677
00:58:55.920 --> 00:58:58.079
-Solo. you are a strong man.
-[Ekah crying]

678
00:58:59.000 --> 00:59:01.519
-You are a strong man.
-[Ekah continues crying]

679
00:59:03.119 --> 00:59:04.440
Solo. you are a strong man.

680
00:59:17.639 --> 00:59:18.639
[Solomon] Bihbih!

681
00:59:22.840 --> 00:59:24.079
[in English] Teacher Bihbih?

682
00:59:24.159 --> 00:59:25.599
[door unlocks]

683
00:59:31.039 --> 00:59:32.079
Mr. Solomon--

684
00:59:33.960 --> 00:59:36.519
[in Kamtok] I want to warn you
to stay away from my family.

685
00:59:38.320 --> 00:59:40.199
Take your madness somewhere else.

686
00:59:40.920 --> 00:59:41.920
Do you hear me?

687
00:59:42.199 --> 00:59:43.199
You hear. no?

688
00:59:46.760 --> 00:59:48.880
Don't put your madness
in my daughter's head.

689
00:59:52.840 --> 00:59:54.679
I love her the way she is.

690
00:59:56.519 --> 00:59:57.840
I'm warning you for the last time.

691
01:00:02.760 --> 01:00:04.840
["Help Me" by Belvia playing]

692
01:00:11.199 --> 01:00:13.960
[Ekah groans]

693
01:00:27.159 --> 01:00:30.119
[groaning continues]

694
01:01:07.880 --> 01:01:09.880
This is what I don't like.

695
01:01:12.880 --> 01:01:13.719
[in English] See your back.

696
01:01:18.719 --> 01:01:20.800
[in Kamtok] You are becoming too stubborn.

697
01:01:22.159 --> 01:01:23.000
[in English] I don't like.

698
01:01:26.880 --> 01:01:28.840
[Ekah groans]

699
01:01:47.320 --> 01:01:49.079
[in Kamtok]
"Little mother." is it painful?

700
01:01:50.280 --> 01:01:51.159
Is it painful?

701
01:01:55.159 --> 01:01:56.039
Sorry.

702
01:01:57.920 --> 01:01:59.760
I'm so sorry. my "little mother."

703
01:02:00.880 --> 01:02:02.079
[in English] You hear?

704
01:02:02.159 --> 01:02:03.039
Huh.

705
01:02:04.199 --> 01:02:05.159
[in Kamtok] Sorry.

706
01:02:06.800 --> 01:02:09.519
["Day &amp; Night" by Ewube playing]

707
01:02:19.079 --> 01:02:22.039
["Day &amp; Night" by Ewube continues]

708
01:02:33.960 --> 01:02:35.360
[no audible dialogue]

709
01:02:44.320 --> 01:02:45.159
How was fishing?

710
01:02:46.039 --> 01:02:47.119
It was good.

711
01:02:47.800 --> 01:02:49.960
Ekah didn't follow you today.

712
01:02:50.039 --> 01:02:52.679
Ekah got me really angry.
I got her well beaten.

713
01:02:53.159 --> 01:02:54.440
She was well beaten.

714
01:02:55.599 --> 01:02:57.039
I witnessed it.

715
01:02:57.119 --> 01:02:58.119
You did the right thing.

716
01:02:58.559 --> 01:03:00.840
I do the same to my boys
when they are stubborn.

717
01:03:01.679 --> 01:03:05.119
Anchor the canoe on the other side.

718
01:03:06.280 --> 01:03:07.280
-Lucas.
-[in English] Yeah.

719
01:03:07.360 --> 01:03:10.039
When I remember what my Barbara do for me.

720
01:03:10.119 --> 01:03:13.199
and I see Ekah do the same things.

721
01:03:13.280 --> 01:03:14.599
I don't like.

722
01:03:14.679 --> 01:03:15.639
I don't like.

723
01:03:17.800 --> 01:03:20.519
[in Kamtok] I didn't know
I still had this much anger in me.

724
01:03:20.599 --> 01:03:22.480
[in English] No worry. Solo. No worry.

725
01:03:22.559 --> 01:03:23.400
[in Kamtok] Look.

726
01:03:24.039 --> 01:03:25.800
You need to keep this kid on her toes.

727
01:03:26.760 --> 01:03:29.719
Don't let her become
like your wife. Barbara.

728
01:03:31.599 --> 01:03:34.320
If I were you.
I would desecrate on Barbara's grave.

729
01:03:35.119 --> 01:03:36.159
[in English] Teach sense in her head.

730
01:03:38.480 --> 01:03:40.760
["Holla Holla" by Fhish playing]

731
01:03:45.960 --> 01:03:48.519
♪ Turn out. turn out the lights
Turn out the lights ♪

732
01:03:48.599 --> 01:03:50.119
♪ Let it shine ♪

733
01:03:50.199 --> 01:03:52.800
♪ I know I've been quiet for too long ♪

734
01:03:52.880 --> 01:03:53.960
♪ But I'm done... ♪

735
01:03:59.320 --> 01:04:00.719
Hey. sir. Welcome back.

736
01:04:01.320 --> 01:04:02.159
[man] Thank you.

737
01:04:03.559 --> 01:04:05.239
So how are you managing with the school?

738
01:04:05.719 --> 01:04:08.039
Everything is going on fine
in your absence. sir.

739
01:04:08.119 --> 01:04:09.000
Good.

740
01:04:09.719 --> 01:04:10.679
Madam Bih.

741
01:04:10.760 --> 01:04:13.159
You're aware that this school

742
01:04:13.239 --> 01:04:15.239
was established out of sweat.
tears. and blood.

743
01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:19.199
I fought through a battle of hell
to get these fish people.

744
01:04:19.280 --> 01:04:21.079
to establish the roots of the school here.

745
01:04:21.960 --> 01:04:25.000
I will do everything possible
not to get into trouble with them.

746
01:04:26.400 --> 01:04:27.440
OK?

747
01:04:28.320 --> 01:04:29.519
Of course. sir. We will.

748
01:04:30.079 --> 01:04:33.639
Now I have been informed that
there's a girl here by the name of Ekah.

749
01:04:33.719 --> 01:04:36.199
who has been attending classes
without her father's permission--

750
01:04:36.280 --> 01:04:38.800
-I can exp--
-I am still talking.

751
01:04:40.880 --> 01:04:43.320
We'll not establish
any confrontational habits

752
01:04:43.400 --> 01:04:44.920
in front of these people.

753
01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:48.000
No child will step his or her feet
on these premises

754
01:04:48.079 --> 01:04:49.760
without their parents' consent.

755
01:04:50.360 --> 01:04:51.360
Is that understood?

756
01:04:51.960 --> 01:04:53.039
Madam Bih.

757
01:04:53.119 --> 01:04:55.360
I chose you as the lone teacher
of this school.

758
01:04:55.440 --> 01:04:58.840
not because your performance
was outstanding amongst delegation.

759
01:04:58.920 --> 01:05:00.119
but because of your firmness.

760
01:05:00.760 --> 01:05:01.599
Please.

761
01:05:01.679 --> 01:05:02.599
I beg of you.

762
01:05:03.079 --> 01:05:04.679
Do not make me have a rethink.

763
01:05:06.039 --> 01:05:06.880
Are we clear?

764
01:05:08.159 --> 01:05:09.679
-Very clear. sir.
-Good.

765
01:05:10.880 --> 01:05:12.320
So what were you going to say?

766
01:05:12.400 --> 01:05:13.760
Nothing. sir.

767
01:05:13.840 --> 01:05:15.000
I thought as much.

768
01:05:16.360 --> 01:05:18.840
And how are the children fairing--
Are they getting set for the exams?

769
01:05:19.400 --> 01:05:21.039
I'm doing my very best. sir.

770
01:05:22.760 --> 01:05:23.880
You may go back to class.

771
01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:45.119
[Bihbih] If a boy takes two hours
to clear a hectare of land.

772
01:05:45.719 --> 01:05:52.079
how many minutes will four boys take
to clear this same portion of land?

773
01:05:53.599 --> 01:05:58.159
If a boy takes two hours
to clear a hectare of land.

774
01:05:58.239 --> 01:06:04.159
how many minutes will four boys take
to clear this same portion of land?

775
01:06:22.559 --> 01:06:24.440
-[in Kamtok] Papa. welcome.
-Hmm.

776
01:06:32.760 --> 01:06:34.599
Have you taken the medicine
I prepared for you?

777
01:06:34.679 --> 01:06:35.519
[in English] Yes. Papa.

778
01:06:37.039 --> 01:06:37.880
Hmm.

779
01:06:45.719 --> 01:06:47.679
[in Kamtok] Did you manage to cook food?

780
01:06:47.760 --> 01:06:48.760
[in English] Yes. Papa.

781
01:06:49.880 --> 01:06:52.119
[in Kamtok] I did everything as assigned.

782
01:06:52.199 --> 01:06:53.679
I even mended a few nets.

783
01:06:54.719 --> 01:06:57.000
I think I can go fishing
with you tomorrow.

784
01:07:01.119 --> 01:07:03.920
Huh. heat my food. I'm hungry.

785
01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:05.320
Your food is hot. Papa.

786
01:07:06.039 --> 01:07:07.840
I knew you would be
coming back at this time.

787
01:07:09.199 --> 01:07:10.159
[in English] But...

788
01:07:10.239 --> 01:07:12.199
[in Kamtok] It's good you take
a shower first. before I serve your food.

789
01:07:12.280 --> 01:07:13.800
Warm water is already in the bathroom.

790
01:07:15.320 --> 01:07:16.320
Huh.

791
01:07:16.400 --> 01:07:17.280
[in English] OK.

792
01:07:21.239 --> 01:07:23.280
["Giving Up" by Lesline playing]

793
01:07:33.440 --> 01:07:34.320
[exhales deeply]

794
01:07:34.400 --> 01:07:36.239
♪ Ooh ♪

795
01:07:36.320 --> 01:07:38.159
♪ Ooh ♪

796
01:07:38.679 --> 01:07:40.719
♪ Ooh ♪

797
01:07:40.800 --> 01:07:44.000
♪ Ooh. I feel like giving up... ♪

798
01:07:44.079 --> 01:07:45.199
[knock at the door]

799
01:07:45.760 --> 01:07:46.599
Come in.

800
01:07:52.280 --> 01:07:53.159
Ekah.

801
01:07:53.239 --> 01:07:55.159
-Teacher.
-What are you doing here?

802
01:07:56.639 --> 01:07:58.360
[in Kamtok]
Teacher. Please. I want to learn.

803
01:07:59.239 --> 01:08:02.559
♪ Ooh. I feel like giving up ♪

804
01:08:13.480 --> 01:08:14.800
[in English] I cannot teach you...

805
01:08:16.800 --> 01:08:18.600
I cannot help you as it is.

806
01:08:20.439 --> 01:08:22.279
We cannot even be seen together.

807
01:08:24.399 --> 01:08:25.960
I'm so sorry. I can't.

808
01:08:28.039 --> 01:08:30.800
[in Kamtok]
They say those who go to school

809
01:08:30.880 --> 01:08:32.159
can change their families...

810
01:08:33.880 --> 01:08:36.920
-[in Kamtok] Teacher. please help me.
-[in English] Wake up. Wake up. Wake up.

811
01:08:37.000 --> 01:08:39.000
You don't have to kneel before I help you.

812
01:08:41.039 --> 01:08:43.560
I freely want to help you. Ekah.

813
01:08:44.840 --> 01:08:46.760
But it's not in my power to do that.

814
01:08:48.199 --> 01:08:51.000
You don't want me losing my job. do you?

815
01:08:59.520 --> 01:09:01.880
♪ Ooh ♪

816
01:09:01.960 --> 01:09:03.960
♪ Ooh ♪

817
01:09:04.039 --> 01:09:06.039
♪ Ooh ♪

818
01:09:06.520 --> 01:09:09.520
♪ Ooh. I feel like giving up ♪

819
01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:13.000
♪ Ooh ♪

820
01:09:13.520 --> 01:09:15.680
♪ Ooh ♪

821
01:09:15.760 --> 01:09:18.640
♪ Ooh. I feel like giving up ♪

822
01:09:18.720 --> 01:09:20.359
♪ Ooh ♪

823
01:09:20.439 --> 01:09:22.640
♪ Ooh ♪

824
01:09:22.720 --> 01:09:24.079
♪ Ooh... ♪

825
01:09:24.159 --> 01:09:26.399
[suspenseful music playing]

826
01:09:48.840 --> 01:09:49.680
Mr. Mustapha.

827
01:09:50.960 --> 01:09:51.800
Hey.

828
01:09:51.880 --> 01:09:52.920
[in Kamtok] How are you?

829
01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:54.720
Have you brought my brother's money?

830
01:09:57.039 --> 01:09:58.439
Mr. Sule. greetings.

831
01:10:00.119 --> 01:10:01.439
Have you brought my money?

832
01:10:02.359 --> 01:10:03.239
Mr. Sule.

833
01:10:05.119 --> 01:10:06.439
You are a good man.

834
01:10:07.119 --> 01:10:08.640
A good man like me.

835
01:10:09.239 --> 01:10:11.960
That's why I have come to see you.

836
01:10:12.039 --> 01:10:15.600
so together
we can come to a one-time solution.

837
01:10:17.640 --> 01:10:18.520
Lucas.

838
01:10:19.960 --> 01:10:22.439
Many days have elapsed.
and you still haven't brought my money.

839
01:10:22.520 --> 01:10:23.359
Exactly.

840
01:10:23.439 --> 01:10:26.920
-You think I'm stupid. right?
-[in English] No. No...

841
01:10:27.800 --> 01:10:30.039
[in Kamtok] I can call two of my boys.
to roughen you up.

842
01:10:30.119 --> 01:10:30.960
Yes.

843
01:10:32.680 --> 01:10:36.279
I think it's time I allow Mustapha
to deal with you.

844
01:10:36.359 --> 01:10:37.199
Right.

845
01:10:38.399 --> 01:10:39.319
Mr. Sule.

846
01:10:40.159 --> 01:10:42.239
I came here for a reason.

847
01:10:42.319 --> 01:10:45.119
Please. just listen to me.

848
01:10:45.199 --> 01:10:48.119
What I have to tell you
is better than money.

849
01:10:48.199 --> 01:10:49.279
[Mustapha. in Arabic] Truthfully. Lucas...

850
01:10:50.039 --> 01:10:51.680
[in Kamtok] You take us for fools?

851
01:10:52.479 --> 01:10:54.039
We are not foolish.

852
01:10:54.920 --> 01:10:56.000
[in Arabic] I swear.

853
01:10:56.079 --> 01:10:57.960
[in Kamtok]
Sule. this guy wants to sell us wood.

854
01:10:58.720 --> 01:11:01.880
No. I don't want to sell you wood.
Mr. Sule. look.

855
01:11:03.279 --> 01:11:04.880
You have a good heart.

856
01:11:05.479 --> 01:11:08.680
You have a good heart.
Just like that of Jesus Christ.

857
01:11:08.760 --> 01:11:11.119
Like Jesus Christ?

858
01:11:11.199 --> 01:11:12.279
-Jesus Christ?
-[in English] No.

859
01:11:12.359 --> 01:11:13.600
-[in Kamtok] You call me Jesus Christ?
-[in English] No. No.

860
01:11:13.680 --> 01:11:17.119
[in Kamtok] I wanted to say. you have
a good heart like Prophet Muhammad.

861
01:11:18.920 --> 01:11:21.800
Both of you have a heart
like that of Prophet Muhammad.

862
01:11:23.359 --> 01:11:24.399
That's what I wanted to say.

863
01:11:24.840 --> 01:11:25.960
OK.

864
01:11:27.840 --> 01:11:29.680
You say I have a heart.

865
01:11:30.880 --> 01:11:34.000
-like that of Prophet Muhammad?
-Yes. that's true.

866
01:11:34.079 --> 01:11:36.279
A good heart like that
of Holy Prophet Muhammad. I swear.

867
01:11:36.840 --> 01:11:38.039
[Mustapha] OK.

868
01:11:40.159 --> 01:11:42.159
What do you want to tell me.
that is better than my money?

869
01:11:48.560 --> 01:11:49.880
Hey! Stop right there.

870
01:11:52.840 --> 01:11:57.079
It's a private talk. just our ears.

871
01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:00.560
Very private talk.

872
01:12:10.399 --> 01:12:12.000
[no audible dialoge]

873
01:12:31.960 --> 01:12:34.239
-Lucas.
-[laughter]

874
01:12:34.319 --> 01:12:36.000
Lucas.

875
01:12:43.079 --> 01:12:44.239
Is it a good deal?

876
01:12:50.680 --> 01:12:53.239
[in English] Who can come up to the board
and show us how to solve this?

877
01:12:54.319 --> 01:12:55.199
Anyone?

878
01:12:59.800 --> 01:13:01.239
Can someone come up to the board

879
01:13:01.319 --> 01:13:03.640
and show us how to solve
this simple problem?

880
01:13:04.399 --> 01:13:06.640
This is something
we have been studying for weeks.

881
01:13:06.720 --> 01:13:09.760
and this is the same thing
that will come in your exams next week.

882
01:13:12.840 --> 01:13:16.239
Can anyone come up to the board
and show us how to solve this?

883
01:13:17.680 --> 01:13:19.359
I taught you this some weeks ago.

884
01:13:19.439 --> 01:13:22.319
so everybody should be able
to come to the board to solve this.

885
01:13:24.119 --> 01:13:25.640
Everybody down on your knees.

886
01:13:27.479 --> 01:13:28.359
Simple problem.

887
01:13:28.439 --> 01:13:30.680
I taught you this a while ago
and nobody can remember.

888
01:13:30.760 --> 01:13:31.760
Show me your hand.

889
01:13:32.560 --> 01:13:33.399
Show me your hand.

890
01:13:34.800 --> 01:13:37.119
Next. next... show me your hand.

891
01:13:38.199 --> 01:13:41.039
["Bonbon Sifflet" by Fhish playing]

892
01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:15.840
Ahh!

893
01:14:16.800 --> 01:14:17.640
Barbara.

894
01:14:18.920 --> 01:14:20.119
How you come back so quick so?

895
01:14:21.239 --> 01:14:22.079
-[in Kamtok] How did the exams go?
-Solomon.

896
01:14:22.159 --> 01:14:23.279
I told you my name is not Barbara.

897
01:14:23.760 --> 01:14:24.960
[in English] Call me Barbie. please.

898
01:14:25.399 --> 01:14:26.640
[in Kamtok] OK.

899
01:14:26.720 --> 01:14:27.760
[in English] Sorry.

900
01:14:27.840 --> 01:14:28.680
But you write well?

901
01:14:30.520 --> 01:14:31.359
[in Kamtok] Is there food?

902
01:14:31.920 --> 01:14:34.359
There is. but it's still cold.

903
01:14:35.479 --> 01:14:37.920
[in English] So you expect me to come back
from school and eat cold food?

904
01:14:38.399 --> 01:14:39.279
Mm.

905
01:14:40.720 --> 01:14:42.680
If you wait. ma'a.
I finish sewing my trousa.

906
01:14:42.760 --> 01:14:43.920
I-I will warm it for you.

907
01:14:47.000 --> 01:14:48.760
It is not "trousa."

908
01:14:48.840 --> 01:14:50.479
It's "trouser."

909
01:14:52.239 --> 01:14:53.079
"Trousa."

910
01:14:53.720 --> 01:14:54.760
Trouser.

911
01:14:55.880 --> 01:14:58.359
Why is it so difficult for you
to understand simple teachings?

912
01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.960
Illiteracy. they say.
is brother to madness.

913
01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:09.840
Nah.

914
01:15:10.600 --> 01:15:11.880
[in Wum]
It can't happen to my daughter...

915
01:15:13.039 --> 01:15:14.239
Not my daughter.

916
01:15:16.359 --> 01:15:17.479
[in English] Nonsense.

917
01:15:21.840 --> 01:15:22.960
[in Wum] Who's a big fool now?

918
01:15:23.760 --> 01:15:24.640
Definitely not me.

919
01:15:33.960 --> 01:15:34.800
"Trousa."

920
01:15:39.319 --> 01:15:40.279
"Trousa!"

921
01:16:15.760 --> 01:16:16.600
Ekah.

922
01:16:17.479 --> 01:16:18.840
[in English]
What are you doing here at this time?

923
01:16:19.560 --> 01:16:22.079
I thought I told you
we cannot be seen together.

924
01:16:23.239 --> 01:16:24.479
Yes. teacher.

925
01:16:24.560 --> 01:16:26.760
Then what are you doing
here at this time. alone?

926
01:16:32.159 --> 01:16:33.119
This.

927
01:16:34.439 --> 01:16:35.600
What about it?

928
01:16:42.760 --> 01:16:43.680
"One...

929
01:16:46.199 --> 01:16:47.399
[reading with difficulty]
c'ild.

930
01:16:48.840 --> 01:16:51.800
one teac'er.

931
01:16:52.640 --> 01:16:53.560
one...

932
01:16:55.840 --> 01:16:56.880
book.

933
01:16:57.720 --> 01:17:00.359
and one pen.

934
01:17:01.399 --> 01:17:04.960
can "cange" the world."

935
01:17:06.239 --> 01:17:09.039
"If one man can...

936
01:17:09.560 --> 01:17:13.479
des-- destroy the world.

937
01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:17.399
-why can't..."
-Let me see.

938
01:17:24.720 --> 01:17:28.840
You're good in calculations. but you're
still lagging in reading and spelling.

939
01:17:31.680 --> 01:17:34.279
Teacher. I beg. teach me.

940
01:17:35.479 --> 01:17:36.840
Ekah. I thought I told you we can't--

941
01:17:36.920 --> 01:17:39.439
[in Kamtok] I will do whatever you want.

942
01:17:50.960 --> 01:17:52.600
[Bihbih. in English]
Just teaching how to sound.

943
01:17:53.319 --> 01:17:55.920
-This is "S."
-[repeating]

944
01:17:56.680 --> 01:17:58.319
-Do you remember this one?
-"H."

945
01:17:58.399 --> 01:17:59.720
OK. good.

946
01:17:59.800 --> 01:18:02.359
If you put it together.
it will give you "sh."

947
01:18:02.439 --> 01:18:03.760
-"Shh."
-"Shh!"

948
01:18:03.840 --> 01:18:04.840
[both shushing]

949
01:18:04.920 --> 01:18:06.720
You have to put your mouth like this.
"Shh."

950
01:18:06.800 --> 01:18:07.680
"Shh."

951
01:18:08.520 --> 01:18:11.119
["Yuti" by Vernyuy Tina ft Kikoh playing]

952
01:18:19.479 --> 01:18:21.079
[inaudible dialog]

953
01:19:03.920 --> 01:19:04.960
OK.

954
01:19:08.560 --> 01:19:10.640
[reading with clarity]
"One teacher.

955
01:19:11.239 --> 01:19:13.199
one book.

956
01:19:13.760 --> 01:19:16.199
and one pen

957
01:19:16.279 --> 01:19:18.319
can change...

958
01:19:18.920 --> 01:19:19.760
the world."

959
01:19:19.840 --> 01:19:22.760
-Good. Go on.
-"If one man

960
01:19:22.840 --> 01:19:23.680
...can...

961
01:19:24.319 --> 01:19:27.680
destroy the world.

962
01:19:28.319 --> 01:19:31.520
why can't one girl

963
01:19:32.079 --> 01:19:34.640
-change it?"
-Great!

964
01:19:35.840 --> 01:19:36.960
That's good.

965
01:19:37.039 --> 01:19:39.479
Yay! Come. Wow.

966
01:19:39.560 --> 01:19:40.920
I'm so happy.

967
01:19:41.439 --> 01:19:42.439
You read it.

968
01:19:43.199 --> 01:19:44.199
Wow.

969
01:19:44.399 --> 01:19:45.600
Yay.

970
01:19:45.680 --> 01:19:46.680
Come.

971
01:19:48.039 --> 01:19:49.319
I'm so happy.

972
01:19:50.319 --> 01:19:51.199
[exhales deeply]

973
01:19:52.159 --> 01:19:54.119
You're awesome. You're so great.

974
01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:59.319
"If one man can destroy the world.

975
01:19:59.399 --> 01:20:02.680
why can't one girl change it?”

976
01:20:02.760 --> 01:20:03.600
[thuds]

977
01:20:06.640 --> 01:20:08.439
[footsteps]

978
01:20:10.880 --> 01:20:13.199
[suspenseful music playing]

979
01:20:27.800 --> 01:20:28.680
[in Kamtok] What were you doing?

980
01:20:31.399 --> 01:20:33.039
-[in English] Me?
-Yes. you.

981
01:20:33.119 --> 01:20:34.039
[in Kamtok] What were you doing?

982
01:20:35.800 --> 01:20:37.760
I was... fixing the bed.

983
01:21:08.479 --> 01:21:11.039
Let me rush to the meeting
before it starts raining.

984
01:21:11.640 --> 01:21:13.279
You understand? Huh. I will be back.

985
01:21:17.920 --> 01:21:20.119
["Yuti" by Vernyuy Tina
ft Kikoh continues]

986
01:23:20.479 --> 01:23:21.319
[in English] Are you done?

987
01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:32.479
I will check it when I rest. OK?

988
01:23:34.800 --> 01:23:36.239
-Teacher.
-Yes?

989
01:23:36.880 --> 01:23:38.199
If I ask you a question?

990
01:23:38.800 --> 01:23:39.640
Go on.

991
01:23:44.760 --> 01:23:45.640
This girl.

992
01:23:46.479 --> 01:23:47.319
Hmm?

993
01:23:50.359 --> 01:23:51.199
Malala?

994
01:23:53.239 --> 01:23:56.119
[singing Wum songs]

995
01:24:25.800 --> 01:24:27.520
[whispers]

996
01:24:38.920 --> 01:24:42.039
[Bihbih]
Malala Yousafzai is a Pakistani girl.

997
01:24:42.520 --> 01:24:45.079
who became an advocate
for girls' education.

998
01:24:45.800 --> 01:24:47.479
even when since she was still young.

999
01:24:48.960 --> 01:24:52.319
This resulted to the Taliban
terrorist group

1000
01:24:52.399 --> 01:24:54.760
issuing a death threat against her.

1001
01:24:56.479 --> 01:24:59.439
[sighs]

1002
01:25:00.079 --> 01:25:02.239
She was known for her focus.

1003
01:25:03.199 --> 01:25:07.680
her determination and her wish
for every girl child to be educated.

1004
01:25:10.439 --> 01:25:12.079
This dream didn't stop.

1005
01:25:12.840 --> 01:25:16.560
even after she was shot by this
terrorist group because of her views.

1006
01:25:18.640 --> 01:25:19.720
She said...

1007
01:25:20.399 --> 01:25:22.399
"When the whole world is silent.

1008
01:25:24.439 --> 01:25:27.000
even one voice becomes powerful."

1009
01:25:29.960 --> 01:25:33.800
The extremists
are afraid of books and pens.

1010
01:25:35.560 --> 01:25:38.520
The power of education frightens them.

1011
01:25:41.479 --> 01:25:44.119
They are afraid of women.

1012
01:25:50.680 --> 01:25:51.560
[Solomon] Ekah.

1013
01:25:52.039 --> 01:25:52.960
[knock at the door]

1014
01:25:53.039 --> 01:25:54.000
-Come.
-Ekah.

1015
01:25:56.680 --> 01:25:57.520
Ekah!

1016
01:26:00.119 --> 01:26:01.800
[dramatic music playing]

1017
01:26:03.039 --> 01:26:03.920
[knock]

1018
01:26:10.039 --> 01:26:11.000
[knocking continues]

1019
01:26:16.920 --> 01:26:17.840
[in Kamtok] Where is Ekah?

1020
01:26:19.680 --> 01:26:21.760
-Where is Ekah?
-[in English] What nonsense is this?

1021
01:26:22.880 --> 01:26:23.840
Ekah is not here.

1022
01:26:25.920 --> 01:26:27.920
[in Kamtok] You think
I came here for jokes?

1023
01:26:28.880 --> 01:26:29.920
Where is my daughter?

1024
01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:32.479
-[in English] Ekah is not here.
-[Lucas] Bihbih?

1025
01:26:33.039 --> 01:26:33.880
Bihbih!

1026
01:26:34.960 --> 01:26:35.800
[in Kamtok] Where is she?

1027
01:26:37.079 --> 01:26:37.960
[Solomon] I know she's here.

1028
01:26:40.960 --> 01:26:41.880
[in English] We'll look inside room.

1029
01:26:42.560 --> 01:26:44.159
No one should step into my room.

1030
01:26:44.239 --> 01:26:45.159
Hey! Hey!

1031
01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:49.840
[Solomon] Ekah.

1032
01:26:51.560 --> 01:26:52.399
Ekah.

1033
01:26:53.560 --> 01:26:55.800
[dramatic music playing]

1034
01:27:05.960 --> 01:27:08.920
[in Kamtok] She is not here. Lucas.
Let's go home.

1035
01:27:12.159 --> 01:27:13.000
She is not here.

1036
01:27:52.359 --> 01:27:53.319
[screams]

1037
01:27:56.439 --> 01:27:59.359
[in Kamtok] I will beat you until
your mother's bad genes are out.

1038
01:28:07.239 --> 01:28:09.199
[in English] What have you done?
What have you done!

1039
01:28:09.640 --> 01:28:13.439
You disrespect me and you put
this entire institution into jeopardy?

1040
01:28:13.520 --> 01:28:17.039
-Sir. this kid is different.
-So bloody what?

1041
01:28:18.119 --> 01:28:19.319
Listen to me.

1042
01:28:19.399 --> 01:28:21.159
We will not stake this school

1043
01:28:21.239 --> 01:28:23.640
and the future of every other children
because of one girl.

1044
01:28:23.720 --> 01:28:24.880
Have you heard me?

1045
01:28:24.960 --> 01:28:27.680
Hear me out. I repeat. We will not!

1046
01:28:27.760 --> 01:28:29.399
But I didn't even teach her
on the premise.

1047
01:28:29.479 --> 01:28:31.359
Who bloody cares where you taught her?

1048
01:28:31.439 --> 01:28:32.920
Who bloody cares?

1049
01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:34.399
Huh? Oh. oh. oh...

1050
01:28:34.479 --> 01:28:37.479
I can see you prefer your little
tangle of that little fish girl

1051
01:28:37.560 --> 01:28:40.079
rather than the interest
of this institution. Isn't that so?

1052
01:28:40.159 --> 01:28:41.000
I have had it up to here.

1053
01:28:41.079 --> 01:28:43.399
I've had it up to here
because of your insubordination.

1054
01:28:43.479 --> 01:28:44.399
I'm writing against you.

1055
01:28:44.479 --> 01:28:47.319
I'm writing a letter against you
to the inspector of basic education.

1056
01:28:47.399 --> 01:28:48.399
Have you heard me?

1057
01:28:48.479 --> 01:28:49.479
On what basis. sir?

1058
01:28:50.079 --> 01:28:54.560
She is a child like every other.
and she came to me. not once. not twice.

1059
01:28:54.640 --> 01:28:57.960
She has every right to be educated
like every other child.

1060
01:28:59.880 --> 01:29:00.800
Now. listen to me.

1061
01:29:01.720 --> 01:29:03.720
I will not fall
for that emotional blackmail.

1062
01:29:03.800 --> 01:29:04.800
Have you heard me?

1063
01:29:04.880 --> 01:29:06.920
You will not remain employed
in these premises.

1064
01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:08.079
not any longer.

1065
01:29:08.159 --> 01:29:11.720
I will use every connection I can muster
to remove you.

1066
01:29:11.800 --> 01:29:13.319
before you destroy this institution.

1067
01:29:14.359 --> 01:29:15.239
Nonsense.

1068
01:29:16.399 --> 01:29:17.920
Miscreant!

1069
01:29:18.600 --> 01:29:20.800
If you like use all the networks you have.

1070
01:29:22.079 --> 01:29:24.640
And you. what are you looking at.
look forward.

1071
01:29:24.720 --> 01:29:25.600
Potatoes!

1072
01:30:16.880 --> 01:30:18.880
This is not good at all.

1073
01:30:18.960 --> 01:30:21.640
This is terrible. and bad for our image.

1074
01:30:21.720 --> 01:30:24.119
["Oweh" by Blaise B playing]

1075
01:30:24.600 --> 01:30:26.239
This is very poor results.

1076
01:30:29.159 --> 01:30:31.439
This just goes to show
how unserious we are.

1077
01:30:32.000 --> 01:30:33.439
But I've been doing my best. sir.

1078
01:30:33.520 --> 01:30:36.279
Well. your best is clearly
not good enough. Madam Bih.

1079
01:30:37.560 --> 01:30:39.159
It's obvious. It shows in their results.

1080
01:30:39.800 --> 01:30:40.800
Look at this.

1081
01:30:41.279 --> 01:30:42.880
Very appalling results.

1082
01:30:42.960 --> 01:30:44.319
Not even 12 over 20?

1083
01:30:46.159 --> 01:30:48.479
This automatically just
disqualifies us from Bamenda.

1084
01:30:49.520 --> 01:30:50.520
I am not happy.

1085
01:30:50.600 --> 01:30:51.800
I am not happy with you at all.

1086
01:30:52.920 --> 01:30:54.079
I'm sorry. sir.

1087
01:30:54.159 --> 01:30:55.920
So. so terrible.

1088
01:30:56.399 --> 01:30:57.359
Which one is this?

1089
01:31:01.319 --> 01:31:02.560
15/20.

1090
01:31:03.159 --> 01:31:04.119
This is good.

1091
01:31:05.560 --> 01:31:06.640
This is very good.

1092
01:31:07.279 --> 01:31:10.319
Ha. How come you say there
is no one brilliant among the student?

1093
01:31:10.399 --> 01:31:11.640
This is a very good result.

1094
01:31:12.239 --> 01:31:14.439
-Sir. this belongs to Diana.
-Yes.

1095
01:31:14.520 --> 01:31:16.399
Yes. it's very good
and it gives us a ray of hope.

1096
01:31:16.479 --> 01:31:17.760
You should work on her.

1097
01:31:17.840 --> 01:31:20.119
This is very good. Work on her some more.

1098
01:31:20.960 --> 01:31:23.960
-Unfortunately. we cannot. sir.
-Why not?

1099
01:31:25.239 --> 01:31:27.000
She's a fisherman's daughter.

1100
01:31:28.640 --> 01:31:31.800
That is the score she had
in the same exam our pupils took.

1101
01:31:33.239 --> 01:31:34.319
But...

1102
01:31:34.399 --> 01:31:36.520
But. sir. she can still stand in.

1103
01:31:38.439 --> 01:31:39.479
Bih.

1104
01:31:39.560 --> 01:31:42.039
Is it that I talk too fast
or you listen too slow?

1105
01:31:43.239 --> 01:31:46.039
Rules are rules and we are not going
to break them. do you understand me?

1106
01:31:46.119 --> 01:31:49.199
You must do everything in your power
to prepare a registered kid.

1107
01:31:50.840 --> 01:31:51.680
Everything!

1108
01:31:55.640 --> 01:31:56.960
We are going to Bamenda!

1109
01:31:57.560 --> 01:31:59.920
["Oweh" by Blaise B continues]

1110
01:32:13.520 --> 01:32:16.399
[solemn music playing]

1111
01:32:22.760 --> 01:32:24.880
-[Lucas] Solo.
-Hmm.

1112
01:32:24.960 --> 01:32:27.359
-[in Kamtok] Lucas. welcome.
-Thank you.

1113
01:32:28.560 --> 01:32:30.079
Those people have not still
fixed the light?

1114
01:32:31.399 --> 01:32:33.000
They haven't.

1115
01:32:36.479 --> 01:32:37.960
I looked for you
at the seaside today to no avail.

1116
01:32:41.800 --> 01:32:44.399
I decided to stay home
and keep an eye on Ekah.

1117
01:32:46.359 --> 01:32:47.920
She has been locked up in the room.

1118
01:32:50.600 --> 01:32:51.920
How long will you keep an eye on her?

1119
01:32:52.800 --> 01:32:54.119
Until she learns a lesson.

1120
01:32:55.000 --> 01:32:56.079
When will that happen?

1121
01:32:58.960 --> 01:33:00.039
[sighs]

1122
01:33:03.800 --> 01:33:04.640
Lucas.

1123
01:33:06.520 --> 01:33:08.720
Why am I so unfortunate?

1124
01:33:11.760 --> 01:33:13.119
I don't look for trouble.

1125
01:33:13.840 --> 01:33:15.279
but bad things keep happening to me.

1126
01:33:17.079 --> 01:33:17.920
Solo.

1127
01:33:18.399 --> 01:33:22.560
[in English] I think. say.
I know how we can handle this Ekah matter.

1128
01:33:24.680 --> 01:33:26.000
I beg. tell me.

1129
01:33:32.960 --> 01:33:34.079
[in Kamtok] I think...

1130
01:33:35.960 --> 01:33:39.079
we should give her to someone
who can control her better.

1131
01:33:40.000 --> 01:33:40.920
[in English] Like who?

1132
01:33:41.640 --> 01:33:43.159
-God?
-No.

1133
01:33:45.920 --> 01:33:46.920
[in Kamtok] Find her a husband.

1134
01:33:53.479 --> 01:33:54.560
What did you say?

1135
01:33:56.920 --> 01:33:59.439
[in English] You want me to
give Ekah for marriage?

1136
01:34:00.479 --> 01:34:01.479
No.

1137
01:34:01.840 --> 01:34:03.119
[in Kamtok] I can't do that.

1138
01:34:03.199 --> 01:34:04.399
Think about it.

1139
01:34:05.319 --> 01:34:06.319
Think!

1140
01:34:09.159 --> 01:34:10.159
[in English] My Ekah?

1141
01:34:10.880 --> 01:34:11.880
[in Kamtok] Our "little mother"?

1142
01:34:14.560 --> 01:34:16.479
Marry her off at this age?

1143
01:34:17.680 --> 01:34:18.840
That's impossible.

1144
01:34:19.359 --> 01:34:23.680
If you marry her off. the responsibility
will not be on you anymore.

1145
01:34:25.680 --> 01:34:30.560
The shame wouldn't be on you.
like the case of your late wife. Barbara.

1146
01:34:31.640 --> 01:34:32.479
Think about it.

1147
01:34:35.000 --> 01:34:36.600
I don't want anyone to abuse my child.

1148
01:34:37.279 --> 01:34:38.439
[in English] Leave that all for me.

1149
01:34:39.199 --> 01:34:40.880
[in Kamtok] I will fix that.
You can count on me.

1150
01:34:41.560 --> 01:34:45.079
Look. Solo. [in English] I like the way
you'd handle Ekah matter.

1151
01:34:45.600 --> 01:34:47.079
[in Kamtok] You are a strong man.

1152
01:34:47.920 --> 01:34:50.680
A very strong man.

1153
01:34:53.439 --> 01:34:56.399
Our late parents
must be very proud of you.

1154
01:34:58.560 --> 01:34:59.479
Good job.

1155
01:35:00.439 --> 01:35:01.760
You need to keep going.

1156
01:35:03.279 --> 01:35:04.399
Believe me.

1157
01:35:11.279 --> 01:35:14.199
[indistinct commentary on radio]

1158
01:35:21.760 --> 01:35:23.880
[phone vibrating]

1159
01:35:28.039 --> 01:35:29.159
[reduces volume]

1160
01:35:32.279 --> 01:35:33.760
[in English]
Good afternoon. Inspector Sir.

1161
01:35:34.319 --> 01:35:36.520
[man on phone]
Good afternoon. Mr. Anang.

1162
01:35:36.600 --> 01:35:39.359
I trust you and your family
are very well.

1163
01:35:40.239 --> 01:35:41.239
Very well. sir.

1164
01:35:42.399 --> 01:35:45.319
I am calling with respect
to the Bamenda event.

1165
01:35:45.399 --> 01:35:46.319
Dates have been set

1166
01:35:46.399 --> 01:35:50.920
and we're looking forward to receiving
your representative as soon as you can.

1167
01:35:51.760 --> 01:35:52.840
It is next week.

1168
01:35:54.039 --> 01:35:57.359
Nine days from now.
and all eyes are on the new institution.

1169
01:35:57.439 --> 01:35:58.880
especially yours.

1170
01:36:00.439 --> 01:36:01.600
I am aware. sir.

1171
01:36:03.560 --> 01:36:05.439
Meanwhile. the inspectorate.

1172
01:36:06.439 --> 01:36:08.439
is taking care of transportation.

1173
01:36:09.479 --> 01:36:12.600
lodging. and restoration. too.

1174
01:36:14.399 --> 01:36:15.239
Thank you. sir.

1175
01:36:18.680 --> 01:36:20.359
Have a nice day. Mr. Anang.

1176
01:36:21.720 --> 01:36:23.760
You too. sir. Than you very much. sir.

1177
01:36:29.039 --> 01:36:30.640
Who was that on the phone?

1178
01:36:32.800 --> 01:36:33.720
The inspector.

1179
01:36:36.279 --> 01:36:37.560
Is everything OK?

1180
01:36:40.800 --> 01:36:41.840
We had a meeting last week

1181
01:36:41.920 --> 01:36:45.680
and I spoke very highly and proudly
of the school.

1182
01:36:46.640 --> 01:36:48.800
Because of that.
all eyes are directed on us.

1183
01:36:50.399 --> 01:36:53.840
especially with the coming of the
Bamenda Brain Box Competition.

1184
01:36:56.960 --> 01:36:59.880
You speak like the children
are not ready.

1185
01:37:01.000 --> 01:37:02.039
[smacks lips]

1186
01:37:02.600 --> 01:37:03.479
They are not.

1187
01:37:04.079 --> 01:37:05.000
Not even one.

1188
01:37:07.520 --> 01:37:09.439
So. what are you going to do now?

1189
01:37:17.000 --> 01:37:18.560
You didn't get a glass for yourself?

1190
01:37:23.960 --> 01:37:25.439
[Anang] OK. Abang.

1191
01:37:27.239 --> 01:37:28.439
Let's start with this.

1192
01:37:29.920 --> 01:37:32.479
LCM.

1193
01:37:33.439 --> 01:37:34.960
Do you know the meaning of LCM?

1194
01:37:38.039 --> 01:37:39.840
LCM.

1195
01:37:50.439 --> 01:37:51.720
The meaning of LCM.

1196
01:37:57.600 --> 01:37:59.640
OK. let's try something else.

1197
01:38:00.479 --> 01:38:03.560
What about HCF?

1198
01:38:05.039 --> 01:38:07.079
What is the meaning of HCF?

1199
01:38:08.000 --> 01:38:08.920
What does it mean?

1200
01:38:12.199 --> 01:38:13.479
It is an acronym.

1201
01:38:14.600 --> 01:38:16.239
mathematical acronym.

1202
01:38:19.640 --> 01:38:21.119
You don't know the meaning of HCF?

1203
01:38:23.439 --> 01:38:26.640
You don't know the meaning of LCM or HCF?

1204
01:38:31.079 --> 01:38:31.920
OK.

1205
01:38:33.720 --> 01:38:35.760
Let me ask you something very simple.

1206
01:38:36.560 --> 01:38:37.520
Now. tell me...

1207
01:38:38.880 --> 01:38:42.640
what is the past participle of. uh. "see"?

1208
01:38:45.439 --> 01:38:46.279
Seeing.

1209
01:38:47.359 --> 01:38:48.239
Hmm?

1210
01:38:48.319 --> 01:38:49.159
Seeing.

1211
01:38:49.720 --> 01:38:50.560
Seeing...

1212
01:38:51.439 --> 01:38:53.199
is the past participle of "see"?

1213
01:38:55.520 --> 01:38:56.720
Jesus Christ!

1214
01:38:58.279 --> 01:38:59.119
Hai!

1215
01:38:59.560 --> 01:39:01.199
Can-can you even spell your name?

1216
01:39:03.680 --> 01:39:05.720
["Oweh" by Blaise B playing]

1217
01:39:51.479 --> 01:39:53.079
You. you look worried.

1218
01:39:55.680 --> 01:39:57.239
Those children are potatoes.

1219
01:39:58.520 --> 01:40:00.159
Flown out potatoes.

1220
01:40:00.239 --> 01:40:01.079
That's what they are.

1221
01:40:02.279 --> 01:40:04.319
Not even one of them can try?

1222
01:40:04.680 --> 01:40:05.600
Not even one.

1223
01:40:05.680 --> 01:40:07.279
They don't even know what LCM is.

1224
01:40:07.960 --> 01:40:09.359
Not to even talk of...

1225
01:40:09.439 --> 01:40:10.760
a long and short division.

1226
01:40:11.680 --> 01:40:14.319
If you ask them
the past participle of "see."

1227
01:40:14.399 --> 01:40:15.279
they will say.

1228
01:40:15.840 --> 01:40:16.720
"eyes"!

1229
01:40:17.600 --> 01:40:18.439
Eyes!

1230
01:40:20.039 --> 01:40:21.319
Is it that bad?

1231
01:40:22.640 --> 01:40:23.479
Very bad.

1232
01:40:27.279 --> 01:40:28.359
Then. I guess you should...

1233
01:40:28.960 --> 01:40:31.319
just call the board of inspectors and

1234
01:40:31.399 --> 01:40:33.439
tell them you are not yet set.

1235
01:40:35.039 --> 01:40:36.520
That is not even an option right now.

1236
01:40:39.279 --> 01:40:40.319
What will you do?

1237
01:40:42.760 --> 01:40:44.079
I don't know. I'm confused.

1238
01:40:45.560 --> 01:40:46.399
Sweetheart.

1239
01:40:47.800 --> 01:40:51.279
I know you are a man of integrity.

1240
01:40:51.359 --> 01:40:55.239
but I think you should consider
considering that. uh...

1241
01:40:55.880 --> 01:40:58.119
that little kid. uh... Ekah.

1242
01:40:58.680 --> 01:41:01.800
I think she's your ace card at the moment.

1243
01:41:03.520 --> 01:41:06.960
I cannot believe
you uttered such nonsense.

1244
01:41:07.039 --> 01:41:10.079
The school must be represented
at the Brain Box competition.

1245
01:41:10.159 --> 01:41:11.000
Yes.

1246
01:41:11.479 --> 01:41:14.119
That's why he deemed it necessary
to call me in the first place.

1247
01:41:14.199 --> 01:41:16.439
even though the event is on the calendar.

1248
01:41:16.520 --> 01:41:18.479
and I was there
at the planning meeting last month.

1249
01:41:19.640 --> 01:41:22.079
He wants to have it on record
that I failed.

1250
01:41:23.640 --> 01:41:24.520
It will never happen.

1251
01:41:25.199 --> 01:41:26.479
Nonsense!

1252
01:41:26.560 --> 01:41:27.920
Do you know your problem?

1253
01:41:30.199 --> 01:41:31.600
Rigidness.

1254
01:41:31.680 --> 01:41:34.399
Yes. sheer rigidness.

1255
01:41:35.680 --> 01:41:38.279
Anyway.
you either use the little girl Ekah.

1256
01:41:38.359 --> 01:41:41.640
or face the shame of your school
not being represented

1257
01:41:41.720 --> 01:41:43.600
at the competition this year.

1258
01:41:43.680 --> 01:41:45.119
I am off to the kitchen.

1259
01:41:45.199 --> 01:41:46.159
Impossible!

1260
01:42:41.880 --> 01:42:43.840
Ahh. Madam Bih.

1261
01:42:43.920 --> 01:42:44.760
Sir.

1262
01:42:44.840 --> 01:42:46.159
Is everything all right?

1263
01:42:47.239 --> 01:42:48.760
I'm afraid not. but--

1264
01:42:49.399 --> 01:42:52.800
-Would you like to come inside?
-Oh. no. No. no. no.

1265
01:42:52.880 --> 01:42:55.640
Let's-- Let's--
We can talk about it here.

1266
01:42:56.600 --> 01:42:57.920
First of all. uh. let me.

1267
01:42:59.359 --> 01:43:00.760
let me apologize profusely

1268
01:43:00.840 --> 01:43:02.520
for the way I talked to you
the last time.

1269
01:43:02.600 --> 01:43:04.199
I am really sorry. it was. uh...

1270
01:43:05.399 --> 01:43:09.039
At this point. I just-- I've come
to realize the frustrations and the...

1271
01:43:09.119 --> 01:43:12.119
yearnings of a tutor
when she finds a brilliant kid.

1272
01:43:12.680 --> 01:43:14.439
as she tries to impart them.

1273
01:43:17.359 --> 01:43:18.359
Sir?

1274
01:43:18.439 --> 01:43:19.880
I am at a crossroad here.

1275
01:43:21.079 --> 01:43:22.159
Madam Bih.

1276
01:43:23.159 --> 01:43:24.439
it's either we win it all.

1277
01:43:26.000 --> 01:43:27.079
or we lose it all.

1278
01:43:29.439 --> 01:43:31.119
I still don't understand.

1279
01:43:35.920 --> 01:43:37.920
If I may confide in you. please tell me.

1280
01:43:39.640 --> 01:43:41.520
what do you think of this girl Diana?

1281
01:43:42.399 --> 01:43:43.239
Can you...

1282
01:43:44.119 --> 01:43:44.960
vouch for her?

1283
01:43:45.760 --> 01:43:47.479
Actually. sir. she is very good.

1284
01:43:48.000 --> 01:43:50.760
I've covered more with her
than the other pupils in my class.

1285
01:43:51.119 --> 01:43:52.600
She learns very fast.

1286
01:43:56.359 --> 01:43:57.640
If I may implore you...

1287
01:43:58.399 --> 01:44:01.680
could you reach out to her parents
and get their consent?

1288
01:44:01.760 --> 01:44:03.920
Do you-- Is this possible?

1289
01:44:04.960 --> 01:44:06.279
I will do my best.

1290
01:44:07.039 --> 01:44:07.880
Thank you.

1291
01:44:08.800 --> 01:44:09.960
Thank you very much.

1292
01:44:11.159 --> 01:44:12.880
Understand this. that--

1293
01:44:12.960 --> 01:44:16.439
We are not only going
to the Brain competition to participate.

1294
01:44:18.960 --> 01:44:21.119
we must make a memorable impression.

1295
01:44:22.880 --> 01:44:24.840
Of course. sir. Of course.

1296
01:44:26.760 --> 01:44:27.680
Do have a goodnight.

1297
01:44:53.000 --> 01:44:53.840
Ekah.

1298
01:44:54.680 --> 01:44:55.520
Papa.

1299
01:44:56.119 --> 01:44:57.520
Me and my brother Lucas...

1300
01:45:00.000 --> 01:45:02.680
[in Kamtok] have decided
you will go live with Alhaji Sule.

1301
01:45:04.880 --> 01:45:07.159
-[in English] Why?
-You will be woman. my dear.

1302
01:45:08.319 --> 01:45:10.159
-[in Kamtok] His wife?
-Mm-hmm.

1303
01:45:10.640 --> 01:45:11.800
[in English] Why?

1304
01:45:12.000 --> 01:45:13.279
[Lucas] That will happen for all woman.

1305
01:45:13.800 --> 01:45:14.840
You be woman now.

1306
01:45:15.840 --> 01:45:16.840
No.

1307
01:45:16.920 --> 01:45:18.239
[in Kamtok] I am a girl.

1308
01:45:18.319 --> 01:45:20.600
Any girl who is as stubborn as you.

1309
01:45:21.079 --> 01:45:22.319
is not a girl anymore.

1310
01:45:22.399 --> 01:45:24.119
You are ripe for marriage.

1311
01:45:25.359 --> 01:45:28.600
Papa. Please.
I will never visit teacher Bihbih again.

1312
01:45:32.359 --> 01:45:33.359
Ekah.

1313
01:45:34.319 --> 01:45:35.960
This is the best thing for you.

1314
01:45:37.000 --> 01:45:39.600
Everyone knows Alhaji Sule is a rich man.

1315
01:45:40.239 --> 01:45:43.119
[in English] Now fine married.
he go take care for you.

1316
01:45:43.199 --> 01:45:44.239
The story ends so.

1317
01:45:44.920 --> 01:45:46.680
Papa. please. Papa. please.

1318
01:45:46.760 --> 01:45:50.640
[in Kamtok] I'm not ready to have a child.
I will not be stubborn anymore.

1319
01:45:50.720 --> 01:45:54.039
Don't abandon me.
I will never go to that school.

1320
01:45:54.119 --> 01:45:55.880
-Brother. let's go.
-Papa.

1321
01:45:55.960 --> 01:45:56.800
[in English] Papa. please.

1322
01:45:57.600 --> 01:45:59.800
[in Kamtok] Papa. please don't abandon me.

1323
01:46:01.520 --> 01:46:02.680
[in English] From tomorrow...

1324
01:46:04.520 --> 01:46:05.920
I will not be your papa again.

1325
01:46:06.439 --> 01:46:07.319
[in Kamtok] You understand.

1326
01:46:07.399 --> 01:46:09.520
Papa. I promise you.
I will never touch any book.

1327
01:46:09.600 --> 01:46:12.079
[in English] I swear to God. I'm not going
to even look at Teacher Bihbih again.

1328
01:46:12.159 --> 01:46:13.159
Look. Papa. I beg you.

1329
01:46:13.279 --> 01:46:16.159
[in Kamtok] Papa. please. [crying]

1330
01:46:17.760 --> 01:46:20.159
["Giving Up" by Lesline playing]

1331
01:46:22.159 --> 01:46:24.960
Papa. please don't do this to me.

1332
01:46:36.000 --> 01:46:37.239
[footsteps]

1333
01:46:41.960 --> 01:46:42.800
[in English] What do you want?

1334
01:46:44.039 --> 01:46:45.600
I want to see Mr. Solomon.

1335
01:46:48.159 --> 01:46:49.039
[In Kamtok] He has gone fishing.

1336
01:46:50.119 --> 01:46:51.000
[in English] Why you want to see?

1337
01:46:52.560 --> 01:46:53.399
Ekah.

1338
01:46:55.439 --> 01:46:56.640
[scoffs]

1339
01:46:56.720 --> 01:46:59.239
-[in Kamtok] How else do you want us--
-[in English] Please.

1340
01:46:59.399 --> 01:47:00.479
I beg of you.

1341
01:47:01.840 --> 01:47:02.800
Please hear me out.

1342
01:47:04.399 --> 01:47:05.399
Mm-hmm.

1343
01:47:05.479 --> 01:47:08.720
There is a competition coming up.
and she stands the chance to win.

1344
01:47:08.800 --> 01:47:09.840
[in Kamtok]
Ekah is not one of your students.

1345
01:47:09.920 --> 01:47:10.840
[in English] I know.

1346
01:47:10.960 --> 01:47:12.720
But the most important thing is

1347
01:47:12.800 --> 01:47:15.079
we can get her registered
and then she will be a part of the--

1348
01:47:15.159 --> 01:47:16.039
No.

1349
01:47:18.079 --> 01:47:19.239
O-N. no.

1350
01:47:19.920 --> 01:47:20.880
Mr. Lucas.

1351
01:47:21.439 --> 01:47:26.000
She stands the chance to win
150.000 francs.

1352
01:47:26.560 --> 01:47:29.119
And opportunity to study abroad.

1353
01:47:29.199 --> 01:47:30.840
-[laughs]
-You see?

1354
01:47:34.560 --> 01:47:35.880
Oh! Teacher.

1355
01:47:36.560 --> 01:47:37.760
Teacher.

1356
01:47:37.840 --> 01:47:39.199
[in Kamtok]
Those are little tricks for kids.

1357
01:47:41.880 --> 01:47:45.560
Why would they give Ekah 150.000
when you can keep it to yourself?

1358
01:47:46.720 --> 01:47:47.560
Huh?

1359
01:47:48.239 --> 01:47:50.600
Leave this place.
Don't disturb my peace again.

1360
01:47:50.680 --> 01:47:51.760
[Ekah. in English]
Teacher Bihbih. Teacher Bihbih.

1361
01:47:51.840 --> 01:47:53.640
[in Kamtok]
Teacher. please don't leave me here.

1362
01:47:53.720 --> 01:47:55.600
-Ekah...
-They locked me up in the room.

1363
01:47:55.680 --> 01:47:56.600
[in English] ...is that you?

1364
01:47:56.680 --> 01:47:57.760
Yes. teacher. it's me.

1365
01:47:57.840 --> 01:47:59.399
Why you have to lock her up?

1366
01:48:00.960 --> 01:48:01.960
Stay.

1367
01:48:02.039 --> 01:48:03.439
Why do you people have to lock her up?

1368
01:48:03.520 --> 01:48:05.399
[in Kamtok] It's none of your business.
Nobody invited you into this.

1369
01:48:05.479 --> 01:48:08.359
[in English]
Mr. Lucas. this-- this is barbaric.

1370
01:48:08.439 --> 01:48:10.399
[Ekah. in Kamtok]
Teacher Bihbih. please rescue me. [sobs]

1371
01:48:10.479 --> 01:48:13.239
[in English] I don't want marriage.
I don't want marriage.

1372
01:48:13.319 --> 01:48:15.479
You cannot be doing this kind of thing.

1373
01:48:15.560 --> 01:48:16.560
She is only 12. Lucas--

1374
01:48:16.640 --> 01:48:17.600
Hey!

1375
01:48:20.680 --> 01:48:21.680
[in Kamtok] I run this neighborhood.

1376
01:48:23.000 --> 01:48:24.640
I am very well respected here.

1377
01:48:25.760 --> 01:48:27.600
If I ask anyone to jump. they jump.

1378
01:48:27.680 --> 01:48:30.239
If I tell them to eat debris.
they do it without hesitation.

1379
01:48:30.680 --> 01:48:33.920
Don't come here
and try to tell me what to do.

1380
01:48:35.119 --> 01:48:37.159
This is none of your business.
Leave this place.

1381
01:48:40.680 --> 01:48:41.560
[in English] One.

1382
01:48:43.640 --> 01:48:44.520
Two!

1383
01:48:45.560 --> 01:48:48.239
Lucas. you cannot marry her off.

1384
01:48:48.319 --> 01:48:52.680
She is only 12. I cannot accept that.
I cannot accept that.

1385
01:48:52.760 --> 01:48:55.399
Lucas. I cannot accept it.
You cannot marry Ekah off.

1386
01:48:55.479 --> 01:48:58.520
You cannot do that.
This is barbaric. This is barbaric.

1387
01:48:58.600 --> 01:48:59.720
I cannot accept it.

1388
01:48:59.800 --> 01:49:01.640
Cross the line.
[in Kamtok] I dare you to cross that line.

1389
01:49:03.359 --> 01:49:04.199
Cross it.

1390
01:49:06.279 --> 01:49:07.199
What is it?

1391
01:49:18.560 --> 01:49:21.840
["Oweh" by Blaise B playing]

1392
01:50:03.319 --> 01:50:04.159
Hey.

1393
01:50:05.039 --> 01:50:05.880
Madam Bih.

1394
01:50:06.399 --> 01:50:07.840
[in English]
Please tell me something good.

1395
01:50:08.800 --> 01:50:11.800
They have locked her up waiting
to be delivered to her husband. sir.

1396
01:50:12.680 --> 01:50:14.399
Oh. God!

1397
01:50:17.720 --> 01:50:18.600
How old is she?

1398
01:50:19.119 --> 01:50:20.319
Twelve.

1399
01:50:20.439 --> 01:50:22.520
Jesus Christ!

1400
01:50:23.960 --> 01:50:25.840
How can people be so evil?

1401
01:50:26.760 --> 01:50:29.000
Does such barbarism still exist?

1402
01:50:29.159 --> 01:50:31.159
It's a common practice for them.

1403
01:50:32.359 --> 01:50:34.840
Most of the young girls
don't even see anything wrong with it.

1404
01:50:35.720 --> 01:50:37.239
And what really squeezes my heart is.

1405
01:50:37.359 --> 01:50:39.800
how they want to bury such a dream.

1406
01:50:41.600 --> 01:50:42.520
Ignorance.

1407
01:50:43.119 --> 01:50:44.600
they say. is very expensive.

1408
01:50:47.600 --> 01:50:48.439
[sighs]

1409
01:50:50.159 --> 01:50:51.159
What do we do now?

1410
01:50:52.079 --> 01:50:54.560
I can't think. sir. I ca-- I can't think.

1411
01:50:56.840 --> 01:50:59.600
Please. sir.
can I have some water to drink?

1412
01:50:59.680 --> 01:51:00.520
Yeah. sure.

1413
01:51:05.199 --> 01:51:08.000
["Oweh" by Blaise B continues]

1414
01:51:08.119 --> 01:51:09.520
[heavy knock at the door]

1415
01:51:16.439 --> 01:51:17.880
[knocking continues]

1416
01:51:25.279 --> 01:51:26.520
[Lucas] Teacher Bihbih.

1417
01:51:27.920 --> 01:51:30.039
[knocking continues]

1418
01:51:36.000 --> 01:51:37.159
What is it again?

1419
01:51:38.840 --> 01:51:40.800
-Search the whole house.
-Are you out of your mind?

1420
01:51:41.439 --> 01:51:43.279
If I hear pin from you again.

1421
01:51:45.159 --> 01:51:46.079
[in Kamtok]
you will know what I am capable of!

1422
01:51:46.960 --> 01:51:49.640
[in English] Ekah is not here.
I've had enough of this brutality.

1423
01:51:49.720 --> 01:51:50.920
Stop embarrassing me.

1424
01:51:51.000 --> 01:51:52.960
Don't even try me yet! Don't even try me!

1425
01:51:59.760 --> 01:52:01.319
[Bihbih] I said. Ekah is not here.

1426
01:52:16.920 --> 01:52:19.680
I told you Ekah is not here.
now leave my house.

1427
01:52:20.319 --> 01:52:21.680
I said. leave my house.

1428
01:52:22.560 --> 01:52:26.039
[in Kamtok] Bihbih. my brother.
Sule must have his bride.

1429
01:52:26.960 --> 01:52:27.920
Lucas.

1430
01:52:28.000 --> 01:52:30.279
Let's go before Ekah runs too far.

1431
01:52:32.800 --> 01:52:35.600
If I find out you helped Ekah
to run away from marriage.

1432
01:52:36.159 --> 01:52:37.399
I will shutdown your school.

1433
01:52:38.079 --> 01:52:40.159
You understand? I will shut it down.

1434
01:52:49.000 --> 01:52:53.159
["Oya Siya" by Blaise B playing]

1435
01:53:27.239 --> 01:53:28.079
Andong.

1436
01:53:28.159 --> 01:53:29.600
-Hello. uncle.
-[in English] You don't see Ekah?

1437
01:53:30.800 --> 01:53:33.239
[in Kamtok] I just saw her
running towards the seaside.

1438
01:53:34.560 --> 01:53:35.399
OK.

1439
01:53:52.840 --> 01:53:54.039
Can you help me cross to the other side?

1440
01:53:56.720 --> 01:53:57.560
[in English] Five hundred.

1441
01:54:04.720 --> 01:54:06.800
O-OK. we will go.

1442
01:54:10.079 --> 01:54:11.279
[in Kamtok] The canoe is empty.

1443
01:54:20.960 --> 01:54:22.279
Can I add another 500 francs?

1444
01:54:27.319 --> 01:54:28.399
[Lucas] Young man!

1445
01:54:28.520 --> 01:54:29.439
How are you?

1446
01:54:29.560 --> 01:54:30.520
I am fine.

1447
01:54:30.600 --> 01:54:31.479
Have you seen Ekah?

1448
01:54:34.079 --> 01:54:34.920
Ekah?

1449
01:54:35.000 --> 01:54:36.720
Yes. Ekah. she is popular.

1450
01:54:37.319 --> 01:54:38.880
Are you talking about Solomon's daughter?

1451
01:54:39.960 --> 01:54:40.800
She left.

1452
01:54:46.399 --> 01:54:47.960
[Mustapha] Lucas. I told you.

1453
01:54:48.079 --> 01:54:50.680
We have to cross over. There's no time.

1454
01:54:51.840 --> 01:54:53.159
Young man!

1455
01:54:53.239 --> 01:54:54.159
Yes. sir.

1456
01:54:54.239 --> 01:54:55.119
What is your name?

1457
01:54:56.159 --> 01:54:57.000
Kum Peter.

1458
01:54:57.920 --> 01:54:59.000
[in English] Do you know me?

1459
01:54:59.640 --> 01:55:00.880
Yes. grand.

1460
01:55:00.960 --> 01:55:01.880
[in Kamtok] Think very well.

1461
01:55:01.960 --> 01:55:03.600
Are you sure Ekah left?

1462
01:55:04.399 --> 01:55:06.039
Or is she hiding somewhere here?

1463
01:55:07.479 --> 01:55:09.840
She crossed over. sir.
With another canoeist--

1464
01:55:10.319 --> 01:55:11.199
Joseph.

1465
01:55:13.039 --> 01:55:14.960
Do you know this other canoeist...

1466
01:55:15.039 --> 01:55:17.039
What's his name again. I think Efofa?

1467
01:55:17.119 --> 01:55:18.159
[in English] Yes. grand.

1468
01:55:18.600 --> 01:55:19.720
[in Kamtok] What happened to him?

1469
01:55:21.880 --> 01:55:22.760
He was stabbed.

1470
01:55:23.560 --> 01:55:24.399
[in English] Why?

1471
01:55:28.239 --> 01:55:29.439
[in Kamtok] Grand. grand.

1472
01:55:29.520 --> 01:55:32.720
I am not lying. she crossed over.

1473
01:55:32.800 --> 01:55:33.800
She left.

1474
01:55:35.600 --> 01:55:36.640
[in English]
Why are you looking me so. grand?

1475
01:55:36.720 --> 01:55:38.159
You look me as you think I lie.

1476
01:55:39.279 --> 01:55:40.199
[in Kamtok] She left.

1477
01:55:41.479 --> 01:55:44.600
I swear to God. if I am lying.

1478
01:55:44.680 --> 01:55:46.960
let my mother be stricken by thunder.

1479
01:55:49.399 --> 01:55:50.279
Lucas.

1480
01:55:51.960 --> 01:55:52.800
Lucas.

1481
01:55:58.359 --> 01:56:00.760
[dramatic music playing]

1482
01:56:15.960 --> 01:56:18.239
[crowd shouting]

1483
01:56:22.720 --> 01:56:25.560
["Ze Bih" by Achuo playing]

1484
01:56:53.119 --> 01:56:56.199
["Ze Bih" by Achuo continues]

1485
01:57:37.520 --> 01:57:40.560
[singing "Ze Bih"]

1486
01:58:15.680 --> 01:58:16.800
What are you doing?

1487
01:58:20.000 --> 01:58:22.560
-What are you doing?
-[in English] Remove your clothes!

1488
01:58:31.359 --> 01:58:32.479
Remove your clothes!

1489
01:58:35.920 --> 01:58:37.800
[scuffles]

1490
01:58:43.680 --> 01:58:46.680
[scuffle continues]

1491
01:58:53.760 --> 01:58:56.479
[screaming]

1492
01:58:56.560 --> 01:58:58.600
["Emotional" by Belvia playing]

1493
01:59:36.760 --> 01:59:38.800
["Emotional" by Belvia continues]

1494
02:00:01.159 --> 02:00:03.880
If I tell you I am not confused.
then I'll be a liar.

1495
02:00:04.840 --> 02:00:05.800
Me too. sir.

1496
02:00:07.800 --> 02:00:11.000
We stand to lose a lot
if we do not participate.

1497
02:00:11.880 --> 02:00:15.399
We stand to be mocked and
undermined if we send in

1498
02:00:15.479 --> 02:00:16.760
a dormant candidate.

1499
02:00:18.520 --> 02:00:19.640
And should we come last.

1500
02:00:21.279 --> 02:00:24.439
we cannot go for a competition
for another three years. so tell me...

1501
02:00:25.079 --> 02:00:27.039
what kind of miracle
should we be expecting

1502
02:00:27.119 --> 02:00:30.039
to at least represent us
in an average way?

1503
02:00:31.720 --> 02:00:34.319
Ekah is completely
out of the question now.

1504
02:00:36.079 --> 02:00:38.000
She got married yesterday.

1505
02:00:39.159 --> 02:00:40.039
What?

1506
02:00:42.199 --> 02:00:45.840
-Oh. God.
-It's inexplicable. sir.

1507
02:00:45.920 --> 02:00:47.239
She has joined the count.

1508
02:00:48.279 --> 02:00:49.199
Oh!

1509
02:00:51.159 --> 02:00:54.720
-That's so sad.
-But we have two more options.

1510
02:00:55.720 --> 02:00:57.560
The first will be a miracle.

1511
02:00:59.359 --> 02:01:00.199
OK?

1512
02:01:04.399 --> 02:01:05.520
Which is?

1513
02:01:06.399 --> 02:01:10.479
We somehow convince Alhaji Sule
to enrol Ekah.

1514
02:01:10.600 --> 02:01:11.600
[scoffs]

1515
02:01:13.079 --> 02:01:16.159
That will be definitely
be an earth-shaking one.

1516
02:01:17.720 --> 02:01:19.159
And the second one?

1517
02:01:21.199 --> 02:01:23.000
What if we don't participate?

1518
02:01:33.079 --> 02:01:33.960
Choose one.

1519
02:01:36.560 --> 02:01:37.600
Commit a crime.

1520
02:01:39.079 --> 02:01:41.800
Hope for a miracle. Or...

1521
02:01:43.199 --> 02:01:44.159
lose the school.

1522
02:02:19.520 --> 02:02:20.439
[door opens]

1523
02:02:20.520 --> 02:02:22.439
-Sule.
-[Sule laughs]

1524
02:02:22.520 --> 02:02:23.920
-Lucas.
-Good morning.

1525
02:02:25.520 --> 02:02:26.399
[in Kamtok] How are you?

1526
02:02:26.920 --> 02:02:29.720
-Fine. How are you guys?
-We are very fine.

1527
02:02:29.800 --> 02:02:30.760
OK.

1528
02:02:32.079 --> 02:02:33.560
So. Sule.

1529
02:02:34.039 --> 02:02:34.880
How did it go?

1530
02:02:37.000 --> 02:02:37.840
It went down well.

1531
02:02:38.560 --> 02:02:39.439
Lucas.

1532
02:02:40.800 --> 02:02:43.600
Ekah made me speak tongues.

1533
02:02:43.680 --> 02:02:45.439
You gave me a sweet girl.

1534
02:02:45.520 --> 02:02:49.199
I can have her all day. No breaks.

1535
02:02:49.760 --> 02:02:51.760
-Very sweet.
-[laughs]

1536
02:02:52.479 --> 02:02:56.920
She tasted like fresh cocoa yam
mixed with palm oil.

1537
02:02:57.000 --> 02:02:58.960
-[both laugh]
-Didn't I tell you?

1538
02:02:59.039 --> 02:03:00.000
I told you.

1539
02:03:00.079 --> 02:03:02.279
[laughing continues]

1540
02:03:03.720 --> 02:03:06.359
I have not been out of this house
in three days.

1541
02:03:07.039 --> 02:03:09.680
The wine is too sweet to go anywhere.

1542
02:03:09.760 --> 02:03:11.880
-I can't go anywhere.
-Sule. Sule.

1543
02:03:13.119 --> 02:03:16.199
-You have done me well. I will be back.
-OK.

1544
02:03:16.279 --> 02:03:19.600
-I have a gift for you.
-OK. Waiting.

1545
02:03:20.600 --> 02:03:21.960
[door opens]

1546
02:03:29.199 --> 02:03:30.399
[Sule laughing]

1547
02:03:31.760 --> 02:03:32.720
Lucas.

1548
02:03:33.560 --> 02:03:34.439
Take this.

1549
02:03:35.079 --> 02:03:36.359
That's for you.

1550
02:03:37.319 --> 02:03:39.560
[in English] Hey. Sule. Thank you.

1551
02:03:39.640 --> 02:03:41.039
[in Kamtok] You paid your debt very well.

1552
02:03:41.119 --> 02:03:42.720
[in English] Thank you. Thank you.
thank you. thank you. thank you...

1553
02:03:42.800 --> 02:03:44.079
[in Kamtok]
When you give me something nice.

1554
02:03:44.159 --> 02:03:45.840
I have to return that favor.

1555
02:03:45.920 --> 02:03:47.000
-[in English] Thank you.
-[laughs]

1556
02:03:47.079 --> 02:03:52.199
-[in Kamtok] You are a good brother.
-Thanks and you. too.

1557
02:03:52.279 --> 02:03:54.880
[laughing continues]

1558
